The Air Jordan 1 Mid White Black Red 2022 is a Jordan Brand’s launch that looks like the 2018’s Air Jordan 1 Bred Toe.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid White Black Red 2022 has a white leather upper. Red accents are present in the collars, tongue, toe perforated toe box, and Swooshes. It also features black overlays, insole, lining, laces, rubber outsole, and Jumpman logo on the tongue. A winged logo on the collar and a white midsole complete the look.

This Air Jordan 1 Mid White Black Red 2022 debuted on 1st June 2022, retailing at $120.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro Midnight Navy GS applies color blocking in light smoke grey and midnight navy to dress the sneaker.

This Retro Air Jordan 4 for grade-schoolers is available in a white/midnight navy/light smoke grey/fire colorway. The upper is made of white leather with black support Wings, a matching black heel tab with Jumpman branding imprinted on top, and navy molded eyelets. The woven tongue tag has an additional Jumpman graphic in red. The sneaker has a two-tone polyurethane midsole with encapsulated AIR in the forefoot and an exposed unit in the heel.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro Midnight Navy GS was released on the 29th of October 2022, retailing for $160.

The Nike Dunk Low Coconut Milk features an off-white tumbled leather upper with pale yellow overlays and white Swooshes. Woven tongue labels and heel embroideries nod to the original 1985 design. From there, a matching Air sole at the base completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Coconut Milk released in March of 2022 and retailed for $100.

The Air Jordan 4 Infrared features a tonal grey Durabuck upper with black TPU mesh inserts, tech straps, and heel tabs. Hits of Infrared on the lacing system and woven Jordan Flight tongue label add a sharp contrast to the neutral-toned base. From there, a white sole with visible Air units completes the design.

The Air Jordan 4 Infrared released in June of 2022 and retailed for $200.

The Yeezy 700 Boost Wave Runner is the shoe that led Yeezy's pivot from a sleek, minimal aesthetic to a chunky, 90s inspired one. This was the gateway sneaker between knit runners like the 350 and the grungy skate look of the 550. The Yeezy 700 Wave Runner features a grey mesh and leather upper with black suede overlays and teal mesh underlays. At the base, a thick Boost sole and contrasting hits of orange complete the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runner originally released in November of 2017, and most recently re-released in March of 2022 for a retail price of $300.

Yeezy introduces a new variation of the 700 with the Yeezy 700 V3 Azael, now available on StockX. The third incarnation of the Yeezy 700 is one of the most sophisticated designs we’ve seen from the ongoing collaborations, playing with shape, line, texture, and even expectations. The outer shell is reminiscent of a race car and an astronaut’s suit with a sole unit that feels progressive and substantial.

This 700 V3 is composed of an azael upper composed of monofilament engineered mesh with RPU overlays for structure and durability. The RPU cage has glow-in-the-dark features, along with 3M reflective detailing on the toe. The EVA midsole and herringbone rubber outsole completes the design. These sneakers released in December of 2019 and retailed for $200.

The women's Air Jordan 1 High Atmosphere follows the classic Black Toe color blocking format with a white and dark navy leather upper. Light pink patent leather on the ankle and vamp nods to the pink bubblegum that Michael Jordan chewed throughout his time on the hardwood. Woven Nike tongue labels and a signature Jordan Wings logo draw inspiration from the original 1985 Jordan 1 design.

The women's Air Jordan 1 High Atmosphere released in December of 2021 and retailed for $170.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Heirloom is a revamped Heirloom version of the iconic Air Jordan One High OG.

This sneaker’s upper, constructed out of leather, features a black denim base, vachetta tan overlays and Swoosh, and black laces and nylon tongue. Branding-wise, this sneaker features an embossed Wings logo on the lateral flap and black Nike branding at the top of the nylon tongue. The upper of this shoe is supported by a white midsole and a tan rubber outsole with patterns to increase the shoe’s grip.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Heirloom was released on September 17, 2022 at a retail price of $170.

The Air Jordan 7 Retro Cardinal 2022 has become part of the sports collection of the brand and is dressed in a white, cardinal red, black, and chutney color scheme.

This high Air Jordan 7 sneaker features a white leather upper with hints of chutney on the heel pull tab and the Jumpman logo on the lateral ankle. Black and cardinal red are featured on the heel tab, midsole decoration, lining, and insole. The signature "23" branding on the heel counter, a black "Air Jordan" embroidery on the tongue, a black outsole, and a round toe box complete the design.

The Air Jordan 7 Retro Cardinal 2022 was released on December 17th, 2022, retailing at $210.

The adidas Handball Spezial Navy Gum takes its inspiration from a 1980s soccer shoe.

Dressed in a Navy, Sky Blue, White, and Gum color scheme, this sneaker features a nubuck suede upper. Other details include adidas branding on the tongue, the trademark 3-Stripes on the sides, the "Spezial" Trefoil logo on the lateral in gold foil, and a branded OrthoLite insole. This shoe has a round toe and a lace-up closure system with Navy Blue laces that match the overall theme. A gum rubber outsole completes the vintage look.

The adidas Handball Spezial Navy Gum was first released on 26th August 2020, retailing at $100.

product name: New Balance 550 Sea Salt Pine Green
Nike Dunk Low SE Lottery Pack Malachite Green

The Nike Dunk Low SE Lottery arrives in a white smooth leather base with black leather panels strewn across the lateral Swooshes, with malachite green Nike embroidered heel tabs.

Malachite green leather material overlays provide the structure for this SE Lottery sneaker´s iconic silhouette and stylized cartoon "Jackpot" Nike logos decorate the tongue tabs and white insoles throughout. Rounding out the footwear design are scratch-off Nike coin hangtags, white midsoles, and malachite green rubber outsoles.

The Nike Dunk Low SE Lottery was first released on the last day of August 2022, and its original retail price was set at $120.

product name: Nike SB Dunk Low Sandy Bodecker
product desp:
The Nike SB Dunk Low eBay Sandy Boedecker was made available as part of the collaborative collection between eBay and Nike.

It has a white base with overlays in the company's trademark red, green, blue, and yellow colors. The sneaker features clear stripes on its vamp, on the heel, and on the middle part. In addition, the shoe features a blue Nike Swoosh on both sides with an SB emblem on its heel panel. Its tongue panel is constructed with a padded cushion with a Nike Swoosh printed on it.

The Nike SB Dunk Low eBay Sandy Boedecker debuted on December 17th, 2022, and retailed at $130.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro Black Taxi is a monochromatic black sneaker with taxi-yellow hits that create visual contrast.

The upper of this Retro Air Jordan 12 is constructed of both smooth and textured black leather. A taxi overlay features the word "Jumpman," taxi containment straps have a Jumpman embossed on them,  and the heel sports a taxi "23", Jordan branding, and a taxi Jumpman patch. The black tongue and insole each feature a taxi Jumpman. The black outsole features a taxi in patterning, a "23" and Jumpman that stretches onto the toe.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro Black Taxi was released on December 3rd, 2022, for a retail price of $200.

product name: Nike Air Force 1 Low SP Supreme Wheat
product desp:
Drawing inspiration from classic work boots, the Nike Air Force 1 Low SP Supreme Wheat features a Flax Durabuck upper with Supreme Box Logo insignias on the lateral heels. At the base, a matching Flax Air sole completes the design. This model was exclusively sold through Supreme stores and their online shops.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low SP Supreme Wheat released in November of 2021 and retailed for $150.

product name: Nike Air Max 1 PRM Dirty Denim
product desp:
The Nike Air Max 1 PRM Mineral Slate is a sneaker with a Nike premium silhouette.

The Nike Air Max 1 PRM has a combination of mineral slate, deep royal blue, and lemon wash colorways. The upper part is made of suede with a denim overlay with flat cotton laces. The sneaker has a padded collar and TPU eyelets with a Nike Air Max woven patch and two Swoosh details, one on the side panel and the other embroidered on the toe. The visible midsole has been yellowed and complements the gum outsole to display a clear faux-vintage vibe.

The Nike Air Max 1 PRM Mineral Slate was released on the 26th of August retailing at $150.

Jordan Brand is continuing their run of the Jordan 2 Silhouette into 2023, with the Air Jordan 2 Retro Lucky Green.

Jordan Brand traditionally stays away from green sneakers, but highlighted it in this model with Lucky Green accents, heel, outsoles and sockliner. The Retro Jordan 2 Lucky Green features white leather uppers, and vintage inspired cream colored midsoles, mudguard and lace eyelets.

The Air Jordan 2 Retro Lucky Green released February 3, 2023, with a retail price of $175.

product name: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Stone Sage
product desp:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Stone Sage features a sculptural EVA foam and algae blended construction that arrives in a Stone Sage monochromatic color scheme. From there, a grooved outsole provides traction and support.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Stone Sage released in March of 2022 and retailed for $90.

The Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink has a full leather build, which makes use of three distinct shades of pink to complete the look. The base has a light shade of pink, with a slightly contrasting pink overlay.

The look is completed by the Nike Swoosh in a bold pink that provides a strong contrast and stands out noticeably on the shoe. In addition to the Swoosh on both sides, the Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Grade School) features Nike branding on the sole, heel, tongue, and inner sole. This shoe comes in Grade School (GS) sizing.

The Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Grade School) was released in early June, 2022, at the retail price of $85.

product name: Nike SB Dunk Low Concepts Orange Lobster
product desp:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Concepts Orange Lobster comes toned in a mixture of three main colors: electro orange, orange frost, and white.

This Low Nike SB Dunk features a nubuck upper with varying orange tones, softly speckled overlays, and a tonal Swoosh accented in white. The interior lining is embellished with a bib-inspired pattern, and the white mesh tongue is embellished with a woven Nike SB tag. The shoe boasts an orange rubber outsole and a cupsole with black sidewalls.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Concepts Orange Lobster was set to retail at $120 at its market launch on December 20th, 2022.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro Military Black for Grade Schoolers (GS) for grade schoolers first was sold on the market in May of 2022.

This unique shoe model provides a modern spin on the original retro item that was created in 1989. It features a white sole and base with suede and leather overlays in neutral shades of beige and black. The Air Jordan 4 Retro Military Black (GS) for grade schoolers has mesh side panels that were designed not only for style, but also for their breathability. The model provides the feet with plenty of support for walking and exercise.

The retail price for this item started at $210 for adult sizes.

product name: Nike Air Force 1 Low LE Triple White (GS)
product desp:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low LE Triple White GS  features triple white leather upper perforations on the toebox as well as two perforations under each Swoosh. The Swoosh and overlays are also white leather. The outsole is white with a concentric-circles pattern and stars in the rubber. The midsole is white with a hidden Air compartment. The midsole says "AIR" in white. A silver tab saying "AF1" is on the top of the white laces.

  This grade school-sized shoe, the Nike Air Force 1 Low LE Triple White GS, was released on April 13, 2021 at a retail price of $90.

product name: New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Light Arctic Grey Purple
product colour: Protection Pack Light Arctic Grey Purple
product desp:
The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Light Arctic Grey Purple is an addition to the New Balance 2002R Refined Future collection.

Designed by a team led by Yue Wu, this shoe features an upper with a breathable mesh base, light arctic gray and purple suede overlays, and purple New Balance branding. This upper rests on a slightly yellow midsole with NERGY cushioning for improved comfort. Underfoot, it features traction patterns that enhance its grip. Like its midsole, this sneaker features pale yellow laces and branding at the top of its tongue.

The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Light Arctic Grey Purple was released on September 29, 2022. Initially, it had a retail price of $150.

product name: New Balance 550 Aime Leon Dore Brown
product desp:
The New Balance 550 Aime Leon Dore Brown has a brown sole with a bright white midsole. The shoe is primarily made from leather and features brown details, including the brand’s "N" symbol that appears on the side.

This New Balance 550 Aime Leon Dore Brownhas white shoe laces, as well as a white tongue that has a brown stamp on it. It was designed with everyday wear and light exercise in mind and offers average traction. 

The New Balance 550 Aime Leon Dore Brown first was released for sale on the market in June of 2022. These shoes were initially sold for the retail price of $130.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Triple White 2022 is a silhouette that arrives in a monochromatic colorway.

The smooth white leather upper of this Low Air Jordan 1 has perforations in the toe box, white leather overlays, and a white leather Swoosh. This sneaker also features a white rubber cupsole and an Air-sole unit in the heel. A white debossed Jumpman appears on the white padded tongue, a black Jumpman boasts on the white insole, and an embroidered white Wings logo is displayed on the white heel.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Triple White 2022 was released on September 1st, 2022, at a price of $110.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Safari Mix (W) explores exotic patterns and textures with its one-of-a-kind construction. Atop a white leather base, the upper features vibrant overlays constructed of leopard-pattern Durabuck, safari print, faux-horsehair, suede, and smooth leather. Vintage-style Nike woven tongue labels add the finishing touch.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Safari Mix (W) released in March of 2022 and retailed for $120.

product name: NikeCraft General Purpose Shoe Tom Sachs Archive Dark Sulfur
product desp:
The NikeCraft General Purpose Shoe Tom Sachs Yellow is the result of a collaboration between Nike and Tom Sachs.

The Tom Sachs Yellow NikeCraft takes on a functional design with a yellow mesh upper with tonal suede overlays and a contrasting white Swoosh on the lateral and medial sides. Orange tabs on the heel and tongue allow an easy on and off. The shoe sits a top a cream midsole packed with EVA for cushioning, while a black waffle-traction rubber outsole is for grip.

The NikeCraft General Purpose Shoe Tom Sachs Yellow was released on the 2nd of September 2022, and originally retailed for $110.

Nike celebrated the 35th Anniversary of the Nike Dunk by releasing the Nike Dunk Low SP Syracuse (2020), now available on StockX. The Nike Dunk debuted as part of the 1985 Nike College Color’s program, a program that delivered footwear in the school colors of 12 popular basketball programs allowing fans to support their favorite teams from head to toe. This Syracuse colorway was among the first collegiate colorways Nike released, breaking the mold for colorways used on basketball shoes.

This Nike Dunk Low SP is composed of a white leather upper with orange blaze leather overlays. A white midsole, orange outsole, and classic Nike branding on the tongue complete the design. These sneakers released in March of 2020 and retailed for $100.

The sneaker sports the white Air Jordan Wings logo on the lateral ankle and Jumpman branding on the tongue and insole. A white midsole and a black rubber outsole with a linear pattern complete the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Lakers 2022 was originally made available on September 17th, 2022, with its retail price set at $125.

product desp:
The Jordan 2 Retro Low is officially resurrected, following multiple newly designed colorways of the Air Jordan 2 Low silhouette in 2022.

Jordan Brand used premium materials throughout the sneakers, including a gray suede and sail smooth leather. The sneakers feature an Orange Melon Tint across the sockliner, heel, piping across the upper, and Air Jordan Wings logo on the tongue.

The Air Jordan 2 Retro Low Craft Melon Tint released March 15, 2023, with a retail price of $150.

product name: Nike Court Legacy Lift White Black (Women's)
product desp:
The Nike Court Legacy Lift White Black W pairs vintage style with modern platform tooling in women’s sizing.

White tumbled leather is utilized on the upper, accented with tonal stitching and a black retro Swoosh. The low-cut collar is built with padded textile, while a strip of beige canvas wraps around the base of the upper. Anchoring the sneaker is an elevated white rubber midsole, marked with a black pinstripe and a debossed Swoosh at the heel. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a modified herringbone tread.

The Nike Court Legacy Lift White Black W was released on the 2nd of July 2022 at an original price of $80.

product name: Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White Black
product desp:
The Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White honors the 40th Anniversary of the Nike Air Force 1 by refreshing the classic design with Abloh's signature avante-garde style. It arrives with a black, wood grain-textured lightweight mesh upper with ripstop collar straps and clear TPU Swooshes. From there, a warped midsole with multi-colored sections of a track-inspired spiked outsole reference past Nike Off-White designs like the Nike Waffle Racer and Air Zoom Tempo Next%.

The Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White Black released in June of 2022 and retailed for $185.

In 2020, Jordan Brand celebrated 25 years of one of their most popular models, the Jordan 11. To commemorate the famed silhouette, Michael Jordan and Nike released the Jordan 11 Jubilee. The sneaker’s distinct colorway was inspired by original sketches from the designer of the 1995 sneaker, Tinker Hatfield.

The Jordan 11 Jubilee showcases everything Hatfield envisioned for the sneaker 25 years ago; a performance product that can be worn easily both on and off the court. Features such as the two types of leather on the upper with hits of metallic lettering and Jumpman emblem add luxe elements to the athletic sneaker. A white midsole and foggy translucent outsole deliver contrast to the black sneaker. Carbon fiber plating on the sole provides stability and power to the wearer’s feet on the court.

The Jordan 11 Jubilee 25th Anniversary released in December of 2020 for $220.

Taking cues from the original 1985 Air Jordan 1 Shadow, the Jordan 1 Low Golf Shadow arrives with a black and Shadow grey smooth leather upper. A woven Jumpman tag on the tongue and a Wings logo debossed at the heel decorate its neutral palette. From there, a grooved outsole contributes the traction needed for a steady golf swing.

The Jordan 1 Low Golf Shadow released in January of 2022 and retailed for $140.

The New Balance 550 White Blue is a redefined version of the classic basketball shoe released by New Balance in 1989. Released as part of the Conversations Amon(GS) for grade schoolerst Us pack, this shoe boasts several highlights.

Some of the highlights of the New Balance 550 White Blue features include an adjustable lace closure, an upper made out of leather, synthetic, and mesh, a cushioned midsole that improves its coziness, and a rubber outsole that enhances the traction of the shoe.

The rejuvenated New Balance 550 White Blue was released in December 2020. At the time of this shoe’s release, it commanded a retail price of $110.

Jordan Brand revisited an iconic colorway with the Air Jordan 4 Fire Red (2020), now available on StockX. This release returns in its original form with "Nike Air" branded heels, making it the first time this colorway has retroed in this variation since its debut in 1989.

This Jordan 4 consists of a white leather upper with black and Fire Red detailing. Rubber netted underlays, black heel tabs with "Nike Air" branding, and black with fire red midsoles completes this design. These sneakers released in November of 2020 and retailed for $200.

Jordan Brand brought an OG Air Jordan 7 colorway to the Air Jordan 3 for the Air Jordan 3 Cardinal Red.

Constructed with white tumbled leather and signature Elephant Print overlays, the Air Jordan 3 Cardinal Red takes a traditional approach in its color blocking and fabrication, similar to the iconic Black Cement 3s. Spicing up the design, sharp Cardinal Red midsoles and detailing pop against the neutral toned upper. Bright orange Jumpman logo embroidery on the tongue adds the finishing touch.

The Air Jordan 3 Cardinal Red released in February of 2022 and retailed for $200.

product name: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Grey
product desp:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Grey was added as a part of Nike’s two-toned Dunk Low collection.

Dressed in a grey and white palette, this shoe features a leather upper with white overlays, laces, Swoosh emblem, and midsole. The grey color is highlighted on the rubber outsole, the woven Nike tongue tag, and the linings. Additional Nike branding can be found on the padded sockliner and heel tab. This Dunk Low rests on a rubber cupsole with the trademark traction pattern. 

The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Grey was made available on the 16th of August, 2022. Initially, it had a retail price of $110.

product name: New Balance 550 White Blue Haze Rain Cloud
Nike SB Dunk Low Pro QS Neckface
model: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro QS
product desp:
The Nike Dunk SB Low Pro QS Neckface is a multi-hued sneaker that tones black and white as the dominant colors.

On the black nubuck uppers of this SB Low Pro Nike Dunk shoe, numerous patches bearing Neckface's distinctively expressive visual sense are the focal point. There is also a number of patches on this sneaker that illustrate several depictions of ghouls, tombstones, skulls, demons, as well as snakes. A white midsole that sits on a black sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk SB Low Pro QS Neckface made its debut in the market on 27th October 2022 with a suggested retail price of $120.

product name: Nike Blazer Low Off-White Black Electro Green
product desp:
The Nike Blazer Low Off-White Black Electro Green boasts a multi-disciplinary, multi-sport aesthetic - a central motif in Virgil Abloh's body of work. Encompassing aspects of basketball, skateboarding, and trail running silhouettes, the Off-White Blazer Low fuses an Air Terra Humara TPU heel piece with a classic vulcanized sole for a unique base. On the black leather upper, punched-out holes are scattered, similar to the Air Jordan 5 Off-White. An accented Electro Green over-lacing system, exposed foam tongue, zip tie tag, and Swoosh tab all add Off-White's signature detailing to complete the design.

The Nike Blazer Low Off-White Black Electro Green released in April of 2022 and retailed for $140.

The New Balance 990v5 Grey is the fifth iteration of New Balance's iconic 990 series that originated in 1982. The 990v5 Grey arrives in NB's signature grey color scheme. Its upper is constructed of a grey mesh with matching suede overlays and translucent TPU side panels. Reflective detailing on the New Balance logo and piping shine when exposed to light. At the base, an ENCAP midsole offers utmost cushioning and support. This model is made in the United States of America.

The New Balance 990v5 released in February of 2019 and retailed for $175.

product name: Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Triple Black
product desp:
The Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Black features a black perforated tumbled leather reminiscent of the Air Jordan 14. Metallic mini Swoosh emblems at the toe and heel shine against a matte background. In addition to Air Max cushioning, G-TEK is also present in the sole, a technology found in the 1999 ACG Air Terra Humara. From there, NOCTA branding moments on the tongue and insole nod to Drake's Nike sublabel.

The Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Black released in March of 2022 and retailed for $180.

product name: adidas Gazelle Indoor Blue Fusion Gum (Women's)

product desp:
Built in grade school sizing, the Air Jordan 4 Retro Infrared (GS) adds some color to an otherwise neutral colorway of the vintage silhouette.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro Infrared (GS) is built on a dark grey nubuck upper with black accents on the quarter panel netting, structural wings, and Jumpman-branded heel piece. Sitting atop the dark grey base is a lighter shade of grey forefoot overlay, while touches of Infrared appear on the molded eyelets and woven Jumpman tongue tag. Lightweight cushioning arrives via an exposed Air-sole unit nestled in the heel of the two-tone midsole.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro Infrared (GS) was released in June 2022 and retailed for $160.

At a glance, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light arrives in a clean triple white color palette, but when exposed to light, the white Primeknit upper changes to light pink and its mesh side stripe to dark yellow. An off-white Boost sole and canvas heel tab add the finishing touches.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light released in August of 2021 and retailed for $220.

product name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Hyper Royal
product desp:
Jordan Brand added a new colorway to their Jordan 1 catalog in the spring of 2021 with the Air Jordan 1 Hyper Royal. The Hyper Royal utilizes material selection and color blocking to provide a vintage feel, similar to the 2019 Air Jordan 1 High Turbo Green.

The upper of the Air Jordan 1 Hyper Royal is constructed with white leather and distressed Hyper Royal suede overlays while the Swoosh and panels around the ankle are made with a Light Smoke Grey Durabuck. Consistent with Jordan 1s of the past, a classic white "Wings" logo appears on the lateral ankle. A blue woven Nike Air label stitched on the tongue, a white midsole, and a Light Smoke Grey outsole add the finishing touches to this retro design.

The Air Jordan 1 Hyper Royal released in April of 2021 and retailed for $170.

product name: Nike Dunk Low Retro PRM Halloween (2022)
product desp:
The Nike Dunk Low Swoosh Shadow Iron Grey is made out of a mix of canvas, suede, and leather materials, coated in an iron grey, phantom and scream green color palette.

The sneaker has a gray leather base that is highlighted by gray suede inserts on the mudguard, quarter panel, eyelets and side Swoosh. It has a tonal Nike branding on the tongue and heel tab. This upper of the Low Nike Dunk is supported by a green outsole and a contrasting off-white midsole.

The Nike Dunk Low Swoosh Shadow Iron Grey was released on the 27th of October 2022 and originally retailed for $120.

Crafted from a breathable mesh and canvas upper, the Nike Air Max 270 White Black now features 270 degrees of visible Air for extra comfort. Drawing inspiration from the sleek Air Max 180, the Nike Air Max 270 White Black features a slip-in bootie construction to deliver a great fit. The sneaker boasts a Max Air unit with 270 degrees of air encapsulated in the heel. The sneaker utilizes lightweight and soft neoprene across the upper to ensure airflow to the foot.

The Nike Air Max 270 White Black was released in March 2018 at a retail price of $160.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Cardinal Red has red laces that lay on top of a white tongue. The shoe’s logo can be found at the top of the tongue in red.

On this model, you will find a red sole paired with a white midsole. The body of the shoe is made out of white leather, with patches of red leather on the toes, heels, and sides. The famous Nike swoosh symbol appears in red leather as well.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Cardinal Red first came onto the market in June of 2022. It had an initial retail price of $100.

product name: Nike Air Max 1 PRM Duck Honey Dew
product desp:
The Nike Air Max 1 PRM Duck Anthracite was a special edition sneaker from the Ugly Duckling collection.

Dressed in a mix of honeydew, anthracite, kumquat, and black color scheme, this shoe features an upper constructed with premium suede materials. Supple black highlights the base, with anthracite hits covering most of the center panel and heel. The mudguard and lining opt for a tonal kumquat, while honeydew accents the Swooshes, laces, and the embroidered duck motif on the heel. A white midsole with AIR units atop a honeydew-speckled outsole rounds out the design.

The Nike Air Max 1 PRM Duck Anthracite made its debut on December 20th, 2022, retailing at $160.

product name: Nike Air Max 90 Recraft Triple White
product desp:
The Nike Air Max 90 Recraft Triple White was first designed by Tinker Hatfield and was re-released for the celebration of the shoe’s 30th anniversary. It provides plenty of support and cushion.

This model provides a fresh take on the original Air Max 90 Infrared. It has a white sole as well as a white base and is made of a mixture of leather, suede overlays, and mesh. On the shoe, you will also find a white leather mudguard.

The Nike Air Max 90 Recraft Triple White had an initial release date of January 2020. The starting price for this model was $160.

The adidas Handball Spezial Black Gum takes on an original 1979 silhouette.

The upper of this Spezial sneaker is made of black suede with a white heel tab in smooth leather. Metallic gold Spezial branding appears next to the 3-Stripes on the lateral side and metallic gold adidas branding adorns the white tongue patch. The sockliner is also smooth black leather and the insole is black with white adidas branding. A gum rubber outsole is for traction on on hard courts.

The adidas Handball Spezial Black Gum was first released on August 26th, 2020 for a retail price of $100.

product name: Nike Air More Uptempo Slide OG Black White
model: Nike Air More Uptempo Slide OG

product desp:
Jordan Brand honored Michael Jordan and the Chicago Bulls' historic 72 win 1995-1996 season with the Air Jordan 11 Low 72-10.

The Air Jordan 11 Low 72-10 boasts a black tumbled leather upper with a signature patent leather mudguard and woven lace loops. On the interior, an embroidered tongue tag that reads "Inspired by the most historic season led by the greatest player ever" tributes MJ's monumental accolade. From there, a semi-translucent sole with red and black carbon fiber detailing completes the design.

The Air Jordan 11 Low 72-10 released in May of 2022 and retailed for $190.

product name: Nike Dunk Low Premium Vast Grey
product desp:
The Nike Dunk Low Premium Vast Grey features a tonal grey suede upper, with warmer tones making up the base while cooler tones make up the overlays. From there, a contrasting cream and grey sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Premium Vast Grey released in August of 2022 and retailed for $110.

product name: Nike Dunk Low Two Tone Grey
product desp:
The Nike Dunk Low Two Tone Grey arrives with a light grey leather upper with darker tonal overlays and white Swooshes. A nylon tongue with a woven Nike label offers flexibility and comfort. At the base, a white and grey Air sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Two Tone Grey released in 2022 and retailed for $100.
The Air Jordan 1 High Bordeaux released in November of 2021 and retailed for $170.

product name: Jordan 1 Low OG EX Black Smoke Grey
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Low OG EX Dark Smoke Grey comes in a mixture of five different colors tones: sail, coconut milk, light smoke grey, dark smoke grey, as well as black.

The leather upper of this Low OG Air Jordan 1 sneaker features complementary shades of grey and black hues. The upper is constructed entirely from breathable nylon and has an exposed foam backing. A white midsole sits on a black outsole that completes the look of this shoe.

The Air Jordan 1 Low OG EX Dark Smoke Grey was first made available on August 26th, 2022, with $140 as the suggested retail price.

The Air Jordan 13 French Blue features a white perforated leather upper with French Blue Durabuck mudguards and a grey leather toe wrap. Nodding to Michael Jordan's "Black Cat" nickname, a signature Jordan holographic emblem at the collar is reminiscent of panther eyes, while a sculptural sole takes the form of cat paws.

The Air Jordan 13 French Blue released in August of 2022 and retailed for $200.

The Nike Dunk Low Halloween GS 2022 comes in different mixes of colors; phantom, safety orange, and black as the major hues.

This Halloween-themed sneaker for grade-schoolers features a smooth leather upper with white hits scattered throughout the underlays. The midfoot panel, collar, as well as toebox are made of white leather, whereas the eyestays, heel overlay, and mudguard are made of orange leather. Orange laces complement the sockliner and go up the white tongue to a tag with the Nike logo in orange and black.

The Nike Dunk Low Halloween GS 2022 retailed for $90 on its debut in September 2022.

Nodding to the University of North Carolina Tarheels, the Nike Dunk Low UNC is constructed of a white leather upper with University Blue overlays and Swooshes. From there, a white and University woven Nike tongue label completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low UNC released in June of 2021 and retailed for $100.

product name: Nike Air Max 97 OG Silver Bullet (2022)
product desp:
The Nike Air Max 97 OG Silver Bullet 2022 comes in a mixture of four colorways: white, black, university red, and metallic silver.

The top of this Original (OG) Nike Air Max model has a metallic silver finish inspired by the aluminum and titanium components of a mountain bike. Wavy overlays sit on top of the mesh base. The exterior of this sneaker is accented with a crimson Swoosh stitched on the tongue and on the quarter panel. Air units are included in the soles.

The Nike Air Max 97 OG Silver Bullet 2022 was released on November 11th, 2022, retailing at $185.

product name: Jordan 1 Low SE Sail Rattan University Red
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Low SE Sail Rattan University Red is a special edition released in a sail/rattan, white, black, and university red color scheme.

This sneaker features an all-leather upper with a white base and sail rattan overlays around the tongue, heel, Swooshes, and forefoot. The Jumpman logo on the tongue and insole opts for a complementary black tone, while the "Air Jordan" Wings logo on the heel opts for a university red flair. A white midsole, a rounded perforated toe cap, and a matching lacing system complete the shoe’s design.

The Air Jordan 1 Low SE Sail Rattan University Red made its debut on October 19th, 2022, retailing at $120.

The Nike Dunk Low Dark Driftwood W comes in four major colors : dark driftwood, black, sesame, and sail hues.

This Low Nike Dunk for women (W) has a lighter brown base that matches the tongue and its attached label. The affixed label on this shoe features the standard Nike logo in a dark black color that is also used by the embroidery that covers the outsole, the Swoosh emblem, as well as the heel tab. Cushioned soles are also included in this pair.

The Nike Dunk Low Dark Driftwood W first hit the market on 22nd November 2022 with $110 as the launching retail price.

product name: New Balance 550 Aime Leon Dore Olive
product desp:
The New Balance 550 Aime Leon Dore Olive is another design from Aime Leon Dore's collection sporting a neutral, two-tone styling of plain-white and dark-olive colorway. The unassuming yet streamlined silhouette is complemented by a mesh-leather upper, a co-branded tongue, and New Balance "NB" logo on the lateral atop a cracked leather finish.

A dark-olive rubber outsole and an aged-out midsole with a matching heel and collar detailing give off the 80s ‘retro look’ that offers the New Balance 550 Aime Leon Dore Olive sneaker a distinct personality.

New Balance 550 Aime Leon Dore Olive was launched in June 2022, retailing at $130.

product name: adidas Gazelle Bold Pulse Mint Pink (Women's)
Nike Dunk Low Championship Court Purple
product desp:
The Nike Dunk Low Championship Purple features a white leather upper with Championship Purple overlays and Swooshes. Nike embroidery at the heel pays tribute to the original 1985 design. At the base, a white and purple sole adds the finishing touch.

The Nike Dunk Low Championship Purple releases in May of 2022 and retails for $100.

The Air Jordan 3 Retro Dark Iris is a high-top sneaker and comes in a white/black/Cement Grey/purple colorway.

The leather base is primarily white with purple highlights around the heel and on the ankle. The shoe also has a black interior, plus a black-and-gray elephant print overlay. The Air Jordan 3 Retro Dark Iris is completed with a white midsole and Cement Grey outsole. The shoe features the Jumpman logo on the tongue and heel, with the 'AIR' brand logo below the Jumpman.

The Air Jordan 3 Retro Dark Iris is set for release in August, 2022, at the retail price of $200.

product name: Nike SB Dunk Low Los Angeles Dodgers
product desp:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Los Angeles Dodgers features a white leather upper with blue overlays and red Swoosh logos. The "Nike" brand name is prevanlent on the heel tab in red.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Los Angeles Dodgers is a low-top sneaker with lace-up closure style. The shoe features a blue and white color scheme that has shades similar to the traditional blue and white worn by the MLB's LA Dodgers. It has a light-brown sole with a pink graphic on the ankle’s right side.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Los Angeles Dodgers was released in June of 2022 at the retail price of $120.

product name: Nike Air Max 90 Terrascape Sail Sea Glass
product desp:
The Nike Air Max 90 Terrascape Sail Sea Glass features a Sail ripstop nylon upper with matching suede mudguards and black canvas Swooshes. At the base, a semi-translucent Air Max sole with recycled Nike Grind treads completes the design.

The Nike Air Max 90 Terrascape Sail Sea Glass released in October of 2021 and retailed for $140.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Bulls is a low-top variation of the Air Jordan 1 and features the traditional Chicago Bulls' red and white colors with a hint of black on the laces and around the ankles.

They are low-top sneakers and feature both the Jumpman and Air Jordan logos on the tongue and on the heel, respectively. Both the sole and the Swoosh on the Air Jordan 1 Low Bulls are red; the red Swoosh atop a white background looks particularly stylish.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Bulls were first made available for retail in April of 2022 at the price of $100.

The "Air Jordan 11 Retro Midnight Navy W" features a monochromatic appearance in a navy color pattern. 

This "Air Jordan 11" for women has an upper made of nubuck, equipped with tonal webbing eyelets in the same navy color. A plush velvet overlay replaces the trademark patent leather mudguard of the Retro design. The lateral collar is embellished with a shiny silver Jumpman. A white Phylon midsole is for cushioning, while the outsole is made of translucent rubber. Finally, the lateral collar is also branded with the number "23".

The Air Jordan 11 Retro Midnight Navy W debuted on 11 November 2022. The shoe retailed at $225.

product name: Crocs Pollex Clog by Salehe Bembury Tide
product desp:
The Crocs Pollex Clog by Salehe Bembury Tide is a product of the collaboration between the American footwear company Crocs and footwear designer Salehe Bembury.

This product features two adjustable and removable heel straps constructed out of nylon, "Fingerprint"  concave ridges for multi-directional traction, outsole pods designed to take abrasion, ridges on its upper side to enable water to channel off the shoe, and holes on its upper to improve its breathability.

The Crocs Pollex Clog by Salehe Bembury Tide was released on 22nd September 2022. At the time of its release, this Turquoise Tonic model had a retail price of $85.

product name: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR MX Carbon
product desp:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR MX Carbon features a pink, yellow, purple, and dark grey marbled EVA foam and recycled algae construction with ventilation holes throughout the design. At the base, a sculptural sole adds cushioning and support. Please note that the pattern may vary.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR MX Carbon released in August of 2022 and retailed for $90.

The Air Jordan 1 Low White Bordeaux was made available as a part of a special edition collection in a three-tone pattern.

This low-top sneaker features an all-leather upper section with a white base and bordeaux overlays. The bordeaux tone is also highlighted in other parts of the sneaker, including the lining, laces, and outsole. A gray Swoosh is on the laterals and medials, and embroidered "Air Jordan Wings" logo are displayed on the heel. Additional features are a perforated toe box and a Jumpman logo on the tongue and insole. The rubber outsole has a linear pattern for traction.  

The Air Jordan 1 Low White Bordeaux was released on August 1st, 2022. Initially, it retailed at $100.

product name: Nike Dunk Low Retro PRM Year of the Rabbit White Rabbit (2023)
product colour: Year of the Rabbit White Rabbit (2023)

product name: Nike Dunk Low EMB NBA 75th Anniversary Chicago
product desp:
In celebration of the 75th Anniversary of the NBA, Nike teamed up with the NBA to release a Chicago Bulls-themed Nike Dunk Low.

The Nike Dunk Low EMB 75th Anniversary Chicago features a Sail leather upper with a red toe wrap and black overlays. From there, a commemorative NBA logo woven tongue tags and matching sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low EMB 75th Anniversary Chicago released in October of 2021 and retailed for $110.

product name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Dazzling Blue
product desp:
The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Dazzling Blue is reminiscent of the 2016 Yeezy 350 V2 Black Friday Pack. Instead of featuring a marbled pattern and sheer side stripe, it opts for a solid black Primeknit upper and blue side stripe with "SPLY-350" text. At the base, a muted Boost sole offers comfort and support.

The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Dazzling Blue released in February of 2022 and retailed for $220.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Stealth, featuring a stealth and white color scheme, is one of the Air Jordan 1’s celebrated versions.

These Retro High OG Stealth sneakers feature a stealth grey hue on the laces, overlays, leather tongue labels, Swooshes, and on the outsole too. The white colorway is dominant on the shoe’s goat leather base. This Air Jordan 1 has a perforated toe box to allow aeration. Also, its outsole is patterned to increase traction.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Stealth were originally made available on August 2022, at the retail price of $180.

Jordan Brand paid homage to MJ’s alma mater with the Air Jordan 4 University Blue. The University Blue colorway draws a close resemblance to the extremely rare Air Jordan 4 UNC PE that was given to Tarheel student-athletes in 2019.

The Air Jordan 4 University Blue features a University Blue suede upper with mesh netting on the quarter panel and tongue. Similar to OG Jordan 4 colorways of the past, the eyelets, heel tab, and sections of the midsole are a speckled Cement Grey. Hits of black appear on the wing eyelets, sole, and Jumpman logo on the heel tab. Two woven labels are stitched to the tongue; one being the classic Jumpman woven label; the other being a Team Jordan jock tag. A black, white, and Tech Grey sole with a clear Air unit completes the design.

The Air Jordan 4 University Blue released in April of 2021 and retailed for $200.

product name: Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK Black Anthracite
product desp:
The Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK Black Anthracite (GS) for grade schoolers was designed with both utility and sustainability in mind.

The uppers are made out of stretchy and breathable Flyknit fabric, and they are adorned by the brand’s iconic Swoosh symbol. There is also a classic Nike symbol that is featured on the insoles. The Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK Black Anthracite is made out of 40% recycled content by weight. The Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK Black Anthracite (GS) for grade schoolers has two cushioning units that are sizable yet sleek. These units sit across recycled rubber outsoles and are bolstered by recycled TPU clips.

First released in June of 2021 at a starting price of $200.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Archeo Pink (W) features a white leather upper with Archeo Pink overlays and Swooshes. From there, a matching woven tongue label and sole completes the design.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Archeo Pink (W) released in October of 2021 and retailed for $100.

Please Note: Both plastic shoe trees are required for verification.
Jordan Brand brings back a monument of Jordan hype with the Air Jordan 11 Retro Playoffs Bred, now available on StockX. These sneakers represent MJ’s comeback from retirement to win his fourth title with the Chicago Bulls and the 1996 Finals MVP. This is the fourth time this colorway has been retroed since it’s original debut.

This Jordan 11 features a black upper with shiny patent leather overlays and red detailing. A red translucent outsole, white midsole, and "23" insignia on the heel completes the design. These sneakers released in November of 2019 and retailed for $220.

product name: Nike Dunk Low Montreal Bagel Sesame
product desp:
Nike is paying homage to the food culture of Montreal, Canada with the Nike Dunk Low Montreal Bagel Sesame. The original release of the Bagel Dunk had customers waiting outdoors overnight in a snowstorm at Montreal’s Off The Hook sneaker boutique.

The limited edition Nike Dunk is designed to look like a sesame seed bagel, with a sanddrift and university gold base, sesame seed coating across the sneaker. Nike used a wood print graphic on the insoles complimented with blue swooshes and heel tabs and a translucent gum brown outsole.

The Nike Dunk Low Montreal Bagel Sesame released January 17, 2023, with a retail price of $120.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Ice Blue Black GS is a grade school release in an ice blue, white, and black color scheme.

This sneaker features an all-leather upper with a cream leather base that matches the laces and tongue. Ice blue leather details highlight the overlays, while a black Swoosh adds contrast. It also has an Air Jordan Wings logo on the heel, the Jumpman branding on the tongue, and a perforated toe box. A white midsole and beige rubber outsole with AIR units complete the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Ice Blue Black GS made its debut on October 15th, 2022, retailing at $95.

product name: Nike Dunk High 1985 Enamel Green Denim (Women's)
product desp:
The Nike Dunk High 1985 Enamel Green Denim W has become a popular addition to the women´s catalog.

The upper section of this High Nike Dunk model has a base of smooth Summit White leather with a perforated toe box and sun-washed Enamel Green denim overlays and Swoosh. The overlays are given worn edges and darker stitching. The color is also present on the padded sock liner and the rubber outsole. Nike branding adorns the insole, outsole, and tongue tag.

The Nike Dunk High 1985 Enamel Green Denim W was released on November 30, 2022 for a retail price of $130.

product name: New Balance 9060 Sea Salt Cherry Blossom

product desp:
Constructed of white and Team Red smooth leather, the Nike Dunk Low Team Red is an ode to the original look of the 1985 Nike Dunk Low. Nike embroideries on the heel tab and a woven tongue label arrive in a classic fashion. From there, a white and Team Red sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Team Red released in May of 2022 and retailed for $100.

product name: Jordan 1 Low SE Homage Split White Black (Women's)
product desp:
The Jordan 1 Low SE Homage White Black (Women)'s design references the 2018’s Air Jordan 1 High OG Homage. The women’s shoe has adopted a split pattern of design.

The design features a full construction of tumbled leather with a white base and black overlays on its lateral sides. The overlays are, however, reversed on the shoe’s medial sides and the nylon tongues. These tongues are marked with the Jumpman’s tongue tags. Air Jordan 1 Low SE Homage White Black (Women) is elevated by white midsoles. These midsoles are paired with contrasting black rubber outsoles.

product name: Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70 Hi Comme des Garcons PLAY Black
product desp:
Japanese designer Rei Kawakubo is one of the most prolific fashion designers of all time. Aside from her Comme des Garçons collections, she has had numerous sneaker collaborations over the years. One of the most outstanding of these collaborations involves her different iterations of work modifying and styling up the Converse Chuck Taylor with her sub-label Comme des Garçons PLAY. Kawakubo’s first iteration of his Converse Chuck Taylors came about in 2009 when she modified the original by stripping back its contrast stitching. Six years later, in 2015, she took the All Star Chuck 70s as her template and created a shoe so beloved that it has been re-released every year since.

The most immediately recognizable thing in shoes from the Comme des Garçons PLAY line is their heart and eyes logo, originally conceived and created by Filip Pagowski. Unlike the original 2009 version, however, the 2015 version and every version thereafter has moved away from the original minimalist philosophy that inspired Kawakubo to start this line of collaborations. The Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70s Hi Comme des Garçons PLAY harks back to the classic 70s Chuck Taylor style but with a high-top collar that snugly hugs the ankles and a black upper, white laces and a white sole and toe cap.

The Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70s Hi Comme des Garçons PLAY Black was released in March of 2019 and retailed for $125.

The New Balance 574 Legacy Stone Island released February 16, 2023, with a retail price of $140.

The Nike Air Max 95 Fish Scales employs both light and dark tones across the upper, which is made of a combination of mesh, leather, suede, nubuck, and canvas. 

This Nike Air Max is covered in an official color scheme of Light Smoke Grey, Black, Pure Platinum, and White. The highlight features are the exposed midfoot on the outsole and the fish scales on the heels. The style is completed with red highlights, 3M reflective details, and a semi-translucent outsole with AIR units for cushioning.

The Nike Air Max 95 Fish Scales was released on October 14th, 2022. It originally retailed at the price of $180.

The  Air Jordan 1 Mid True Blue Cement GS is a celebrated addition to the brand´s catalog for grade-schoolers (GS).

Built in white leather with contrasts in Nike's Cement Grey shade, this Mid Air Jordan 1 sneaker has perforations on the toebox. It also features rue lue accents on the mudguard, eyestays, padded collars, and oversized Swoosh that spans around the heel. It also boasts sports grey elephant print accents and fire red accents on the Wings logo and outsole.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid True Blue Cement GS was released January 14th, 2023, at a retail price of $125.

product name: adidas adiFOM Q Wonder White Core Black
Jordan 6 Retro Low Golf White Infrared
Nike Air Max Plus Social F.C.
Nike Dunk Low Racer Blue White
product desp:
The Nike Dunk Low Racer Blue White features a smooth Racer Blue leather upper with contrasting white leather overlays and Swooshes. A woven Nike tongue tag and heel embroidery nod to the original stylings of the 1985 Nike Dunk. At the base, a matching EVA foam sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Racer Blue White released in 2022 and retailed for $100.

The Jordan 1 Mid Shadow Red features a grey smooth leather upper with black overlays and Swooshes. At the collar, a debossed red Air Jordan Wings logo nods to the original Air Jordan 1 design. From there, a woven Jumpman tongue tag, white midsole, and black outsole complete the design.

The Jordan 1 Mid Shadow Red released in October of 2021 and retailed for $120.

product name: Nike Air Max 1 Travis Scott Cactus Jack Baroque Brown
product colour: Travis Scott Cactus Jack Baroque Brown
product desp:
In collaboration with Travis Scott's record label Cactus Jack, the Nike Air Max 1 Travis Scott Cactus Jack Brown draws inspiration from the Nike ACG Pocket Knife hiking shoe. It features a layered mesh upper with tonal-brown Durabuck overlays and reversed Swoosh logos. A drawstring Gillie lacing system nods to common features on trail runners. At the base, a yellowed sole with a cloudy Air unit completes the design.

The Nike Air Max 1 Travis Scott Cactus Jack Brown released in May of 2022 and retailed for $150.

product name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Oat
product desp:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Oat features a yellow, orange, and blue swirl-patterned Primeknit upper with a mesh side stripe and yellow heel tab. From there, a semi-translucent Boost midsole and pale yellow rope laces complete the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Oat released in October of 2021 and retailed for $220.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Reverse Bred 2021 is back, this time remixing another popular colorway, centered on the familiar mix of Gym Red, Black, and White.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Reverse Bred 2021 features a red leather base accented by contrasting black overlays. The sneaker gets the iconic Nike Swooshes, and additional branding comes in the form of Jumpman tongues, Win(GS) for grade schoolers motifs at the collar, and printed insoles. The sneaker is rounded off with pure white midsoles paired with red rubber outsoles.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Reverse Bred 2021 was released in February 2020 and retailed for $120.

product name: Nike Air Force 1 Mid Stussy Fossil
product desp:
Taking inspiration from the 2020 Nike Air Force 1 Low Stüssy Fossil, the Nike Air Force 1 Mid Stüssy Hemp reimagines the neutral-toned design in a mid-top format. It features a hemp-like woven upper with puff embroidered Swooshes and an alternate, long-haired textile on the heel tabs. Metal heel embellishments, dual-branded tongue tags, and a Stüssy double "S" logo perforated on the toe box complete the design.

The Nike Air Force 1 Mid Stüssy Hemp released in May of 2022 and retailed for $150.

Drawing a strong resemblance to the original Air Jordan 12 Taxi, the Air Jordan 12 Royalty Taxi elevates the classic design with minor alterations in its detailing.

The design features a white tumbled leather upper with a black toe wrap and gold hook eyelets. A new feature is on the toe wrap, where a gold plaquet is prominent on the lateral side. From there, a woven heel tag and matching sole completes the design.

The Air Jordan 12 Royalty Taxi releases in November of 2021 and retails for $190.

product name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Patent Bred (GS)
product desp:
A modified version of Michael Jordan’s first signature sneaker, the grade school Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Bred Patent GS is an outstanding colorway.

Since its release, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Bred Patent GS has earned a lot of market success primarily because it boasts accented details, including an upper constructed from patent leather, a woven tongue tag, a debossed Air Jordan Wings logo on the ankle, an encapsulated Air-sole cushioning, and an enhanced red rubber outsole.

The gradeschool Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Bred Patent GS released in December 2021. It retailed at $130.

product name: Nike Dunk Low Retro Sun Club Multi (Women's)
product desp:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro Sun Club Multi W has white laces and a white tongue.

This model has a tan sole and a white midsole. The body features a white base with patches of many different colors, including pink, orange, blue, and green. An abstract drawing is included on the heel in black. The Nike swoosh symbol appears in bright burnt orange color. Around the laces, there is also orange detailing, which loops back to the heel.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro Sun Club Multi W was first put on the market in July of 2022. It had a starting retail value of $110.

The Air Jordan 6 Carmine returned in its original form in 2021. The nearly 20-year-old colorway first made its appearance in 1991 during Michael Jordan’s ’91-’92 season and brought in a new form of color blocking to the signature silhouette.

The Air Jordan 6 Carmine combines red, white, and black colors to represent the Chicago Bulls’ signature colors. The upper features bold red and white colors that help the model pop while on foot. From there, the upper is met with a white and black midsole, with hits of an icy blue outsole appear as well. The final touch to this OG’s return is the signature "Nike Air" on the heel, replacing 2008 and 2012 retros’ "Jumpman" logo.

The Air Jordan 6 Carmine released in February of 2021 for $200.

product name: Crocs Pollex Clog by Salehe Bembury Cobbler
product desp:
The Crocs Pollex Clog Salehe Bembury Cobbler arrives in a similar fashion to prior releases, being that it has a monochromatic fingerprint-looking foam construction and adjustable velcro heel straps for secure fit. The main standout of the Cobbler is the peach-inspired bright orange color, which isn't a new adventure for Bembury - his first New Balance 2002R featured a similar palette.

The Crocs Pollex Clog Salehe Bembury Cobbler released in August of 2022 and retailed for $85.

Jordan Brand adds a twist to a classic with the Jordan 1 Retro High Royal Toe, now available on StockX. Releases like the Shattered Backboard 1 and Bred Toe have shifted all eyes on Jordan’s "Black Toe" inspired colorways. The Royal Toe takes inspiration from the original Jordan 1 Royal colorway (which released in 1985) and adds design elements of the Black Toe 1 to create a familiar, but new dialogue.

This AJ 1 features a white and royal leather upper with black leather overlays and detailing. A white midsole, royal outsole, and branded leather tongue tag completes this design. These sneakers released in May of 2020 and retailed for $170 USD.

With its subtle details and simple structure, the Common Projects Original Achilles White is designed with casual walking in mind, rather than intense exercise or hitting the basketball court.

This Common Projects Original Achilles White features a crisp white sole, with the rest of the upper being in the same shade. The majority of the shoe is composed of leather, and a serial number is stamped in gold towards the heel. White laces lay on top of the simple white tongue that is free of any logo.

First released in January 2004, the Common Projects Original Achilles White had a starting retail price of $415.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Particle Grey (Women's) features a neutral tone and is dominated by supple suede throughout.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Particle Grey (W) features a Grey nubuck upper accented with fluffy suede overlays. Particle Grey suede covers the side Swoosh and eyelets, while the inner lining is made of white fleece. White laces run the length of the tongue and add contrast to the silhouette. Underfoot, a White midsole and Grey outsole finish round off the look.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Particle Grey (Women's) was released in February 2022 and retailed for $140.

product name: Nike Dunk Low Ivory Hyper Royal (GS)
product desp:
The Nike Dunk Low Ivory Hyper Royal GS is one additions to the grade-schoolers´ collection.

This Low Nike Dunk model features a smooth leather upper with a base layering that sports grey and light cream tones and celestine blue detailing on the eyestays. Other details include Royal Blue Swooshes, a small Swoosh on the right toe, and a perforated toe box. Branding is highlighted in multiple areas, including a tag on the lateral, a woven tongue tag, the insoles, and embroidered heel. A white rubber midsole and a light blue outsole complete the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Ivory Hyper Royal GS was made available on November 8th, 2022 retailing at $95.

product name: Nike Dunk Low Retro Medium Grey Varsity Red UNLV (2021)
product colour: Retro Medium Grey Varsity Red UNLV (2021)
product desp:
Nike re-issued one of its most notable Dunk colorways with the Nike Dunk Low Retro Medium Grey Varsity Red UNLV. The UNLV colorway debuted in 1985, as part of Nike’s Be True To Your School Campaign for the Nike Dunk.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro Medium Grey Varsity Red UNLV features a red and grey leather upper, with grey on the vamp and medial panels and red on the upper’s overlay and Swoosh. Nike Air branding is prominent on the tongue and heel. A white midsole and red EVA outsole wraps up the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro Medium Grey Varsity Red UNLV released in February of 2021 and retailed for $100.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro Midnight Navy PS, sized for pre-schoolers, takes its inspiration from a 1989 silhouette.

The upper of this Retro Air Jordan 4 model is made of white tumbled leather with speckled gray leather overlays, white mesh on the quarter panel and upper toe box, and navy hits. The foam midsole features speckled gray hits and the rubber outsole is gray, white, red and navy, with a red Jumpman. A navy Jumpman appears on the white tongue and the gray speckled heel. The insole is navy and white. A round toe completes the design.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro Midnight Navy PS debuted on October 29th, 2022 retailing for $90.

The sides, toes, and ankles of the Air Jordan 1 Low New Emerald GS pair are covered in white leather. This sneaker also features a rugged suede overlay system that is covered in a light grey hue.

The Swoosh emblems of Nike on the sides of the these Air Jordan 1 for grade-schoolers are made of grey color, and the lacing system and the sockliner are made of a darker shade of grey.

The Air Jordan 1 Low New Emerald GS released on July 14th, 2022, with a suggested retail price of $95.

product name: New Balance 550 Aime Leon Dore Purple
product desp:
The New Balance 550 Aime Leon Dore Purple falls under the category of fashion and athletic sneakers.

This 550 New Balance by Aime Leon Dore in Purple is dressed in an elementary two-tone color scheme that features vintage-inspired details. The low-top features a violet-colored "N" emblem in cracked leather and a white leather upper with a microperforated midfoot overlay. The left and right heels each have mismatched NB and ALD branding. A classic rubber cupsole with worn sidewalls and an exposed EVA wedge on the medial side finishes the design of this sneaker.

The New Balance 550 Aime Leon Dore Purple was released on the 21st of May, 2022, at a retail price of $130.

product name: Nike Dunk Low Retro Rattan Gorge Green
product desp:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro Rattan Gorge Green has a full leather upper and combines a Rattan, Gorge Green, Sail and Dark Driftwood color scheme.

The sneaker also features a Gorge Green on its Swooshes, tongue labeling, inner liner, rubber outsoles, and heel tabs. At the rear end of the shoe is the Nike branding printed in white. Other details include the perforations at the forefoot, and a crossed lacing system in white. The outsole boasts a linear pattern for traction and stitching throughout.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro Rattan Gorge Green made its debut on November 23rd, 2022, with a retail price set at $110.

product name: Nike Dunk High Retro BTTYS TCU
Nike Tiger Woods TW '13 Retro White Varsity Red
product desp:
Nike is bringing back Tiger Woods’ first ever golf shoe, The Nike Tiger Woods TW ‘13, in honor of its 10-year anniversary. Tiger Woods debuted the shoe originally in 2013, where he went on to win five tournaments and PGA Golfer of the Year.

Tiger Woods’ iconic TW ‘13 golf sneakers are constructed of a white water resistant upper, with a black swoosh, and black and red accents. The retro sneakers feature a six-spike outsole that allows for maximum stability and comfort for high performance from the tee box to the greens.

The Nike Tiger Woods TW '13 Retro White Varsity Red released February 16, 2023, with a retail price of $240.

product name: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 SP Vast Grey
adidas Ultra Boost 5.0 DNA Core Black Beam Green
Nike Air Foamposite One Dream A World Grey
