product desp:
The Swoosh on the Nike Dunk Low Judge Grey is white, as are the laces and the Nike logo on the tongue.

This low-top sneaker has a full leather construction with a mocha-brown base color that’s complemented by a lighter overlay around the heel, where the laces go through and around the toe. The Nike Dunk Low Judge Grey’s sole matches the lighter hue on the overlays, but it also has a white highlight between the base of the sole and the shoe itself.

The Nike Dunk Low Judge Grey sneaker was made available for retail at a price of $100 in June, 2022.

product name: Nike Blazer Low Off-White University Red
product desp:
The Nike Blazer Low Off-White White University Red boasts a multi-disciplinary, multi-sport aesthetic - a central motif in Virgil Abloh's body of work. Encompassing aspects of basketball, skateboarding, and trail running silhouettes, the Off-White Blazer Low fuses an Air Terra Humara TPU heel piece with a classic vulcanized sole for a unique base. On the white leather upper, punched-out holes are scattered, similar to the Air Jordan 5 Off-White. An accented over-lacing system, exposed foam tongue, zip tie tag, and Swoosh tab all add Off-White's signature detailing to this modified classic.

The Nike Blazer Low Off-White White University Red released in April of 2022 and retailed for $140.

The Air Jordan 5 Low CLOT Jade celebrates China's appreciation for jade, as its heritage and tradition is infused with greatness. The design features a black satin-like upper with semi-translucent TPU netted inserts and light grey heel embroideries. Attached to the red woven laces, clear jade beads add further decoration. At the base, a midsole similar to the Jordan 5 Metallic and a jade semi-translucent outsole complete the design.

The Air Jordan 5 Low CLOT Jade released in May of 2022 and retailed for $200.

Jordan Brand honored NBA head coach Phil Jackson's spiritual approach to coaching with the Air Jordan 4 Zen Master.

Nodding to Michael Jordan-era Chicago Bulls head coach Phil Jackson's nickname "Zen Master", the Air Jordan 4 Zen Master offers a calming palette with faint blue and pink tie-dye canvas uppers with clear TPU eyelets and heel tabs. Black TPU netted inserts and woven Jordan Flight tongue labels bring a slight contrast. From there, a matching sole with an Air unit under the heel completes the design.

The Air Jordan 4 Zen Master released in June of 2022 and retailed for $210.

product name: Nike Dunk High Championship White Red
product desp:
Similar to classic Dunks from the mid-1980's, the Nike Dunk High Championship White Red carries a more traditional look with a two-tone color blocked leather upper. At the base, a matching Air sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk High Championship White Red released in May of 2022 and retailed for $115.

Seven years following its 2015 debut, the iconic adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtle Dove made its return.

While the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtle Dove (2022) does arrive with the same brown and grey patterned Primeknit upper, rope laces, and grooved Boost sole as the original release, there are some minor differences. The 2022 iteration is packaged in an updated box and features an upgraded outsole, built for daily wear.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtle Dove (2022) released in August of 2022 and retailed for $230.

To shop the original adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtle Dove, click here.

product name: Nike Air Max Correlate Black White Grey
product desp:
The Nike Air Max Correlate Black White Grey is a comfortable yet flexible shoe that provides all of the best athletic qualities while still being stylish.

The Nike Air Max Correlate Black White Grey provides an ample amount of heel support and has a particularly cushioned sole. Splashes of pink and green appear in contrast to the black, white, and grey pattern that makes up a majority of the shoe. The upper part of the Nike Air Max Correlate Black White Grey molds to the foot, helping to provide support and protection while still remaining comfortable.

First released in May 2022 at a starting price of $155.

The Air Jordan 7 Retro Citrus 2022 features a Black Durabuck upper, with citrus and red highlights on the sole. It also features citrus threading all around the shoe and a citrus-colored Jumpman logo on the outer side of the upper ankle. The shoe has a small red strap behind the ankle, as well as a "23" set on a black and yellow background.

The Air Jordan 7 Retro Citrus 2022 is set for release in August, 2022, at a retail price of $200.

product name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Ice
product desp:
The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Mono Ice is one of three from the Mono pack. Each sneaker’s upper is constructed from a new monofilament mesh in Ice blue that exposes the model’s inner cage lining. The Mono pack brings back the heel’s pull tab design on each pair. To finish it out, a familiar Boost sole is added for comfort for the wearer.

The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Mono Ice released in June of 2021 for $220, exclusively in the US.

product name: Nike Dunk Low Disrupt 2 Phantom University Blue (Women's)
product desp:
The women's Nike Dunk Low Disrupt 2 Phantom University Blue (W) features a white woven upper with dark green suede overlays and a University Blue Swoosh embroidery. From there, an overlapping green leather heel wrap and reconstructed woven tongue label complete the design.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Disrupt 2 Phantom University Blue (W) released in February of 2022 and retailed for $110.

The women's Jordan 1 Mid Light Smoke Grey (W) features white leather upper with Light Smoke Grey overlays and black Swooshes. From there, a classic Jordan Wings logo on the collar and Jumpman logo tongue label add the finishing touch.

The women's Jordan 1 Mid Light Smoke Grey (W) released in October of 2021 and retailed for $120.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Harvest Moon (W) features a white leather upper with light brown overlays and Swooshes. From there, a matching woven tongue label and sole complete the design.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Harvest Moon (W) releases in 2022 and retails for $100.

The Nike Lebron 20 Time Machine is a multi-toned sneaker that features medium soft pink and barely green hues as the dominant color schemes.

The woven mesh upper of this Lebron 20 from Nike is contrasted by the fuchsia-colored padded collar that is complemented by a orange hue stitching on the leather eyestay. The lateral side features a turquoise Swoosh with exposed deco stitching encircling it, placed above an iridescent Swoosh. The sneaker also has a guardrail coated in synthetic material and decorated with a design that holds the lateral forefoot in place.

The Nike Lebron 20 Time Machine debuted on September 29th, 2022, with a retail price of $200.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low Flax pays unofficial homage to the classic wheat Timberland work boot with its monochromatic flax suede uppers and overlays. Boot styled two-tone rope laces and top eyelets with metal grommets provide functionality and a rugged appeal. At the base, a matching flax Air sole is geared for daily wear and tear.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low Flax released in September of 2019 for $100, and restocked in April of 2022 for $130.

product name: Air Jordan 1 Low Vintage Stealth Grey
product desp:
Since its debut, Air Jordan 1 Low Vintage Grey remains one of the highest-selling variants in the Air Jordan 1 Low series.

Leather, nylon, and fiber are the main materials of the various components of Air Jordan 1 Low Vintage Grey’s heels. Its white leather base is complemented by the nylon tongue and the distressed midsole. The outsole, fabric linings, and laces of the shoe all feature grey overlays. The wings logo is embroidered in white on Air Jordan 1 Low Vintage Grey’s heels.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Vintage Grey is set to release September 2, 2022, at a price of $110.

The Nike Air Max 1 Sail Ironstone features a mix of four different hues: sail, ironstone, white, and rattan.

This Nike Air Max 1 sneaker in Sail Ironstone features a white mesh base with off-white suede equivalents. Nike's Swoosh insignia appears in brown over the sides of this shoe. The small Swoosh emblem on the lateral toes is also presented in brown. It also boasts cream-colored Air midsole units and a white lacing system that complements its appearance.

The Nike Air Max 1 Sail Ironstone was made available on November 24th, 2022, with a retail price of $150.

product name: Nike SB Dunk High Pro Premium San Francisco Giants
model: Nike SB Dunk High Pro Premium
product desp:
Nike SB Dunk High San Francisco Giants, style code DO9394-100, has become one of the most celebrated footwear lines in the Nike series.

Nike SB Dunk High San Francisco Giants is a product of synthetic leather at the upper and a rubber outsole. The sneaker is embellished in a coconut milk, team orange, and black colorway. It features black with an orange Swoosh across the quarter panel to the heel notch. The white midsole and black team orange at the outsole complete the sneaker's design.

Nike SB Dunk High San Francisco Giants debuted at a retail price of $125 on July 26, 2022.

product name: Jordan 1 Low Eastside Golf Out of the Mud
product colour: Eastside Golf Out of the Mud
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Low Eastside Golf Out of the Mud is the result from a collaboration that combines three colors.

The upper of this Low Air Jordan 1 model is navy nubuck with perforations in the toe box and navy nubuck overlays and Swoosh. One insole is orange and one is green, and both have a white Jumpman logo. The Redstone outsole represents red clay mud. The sneaker also sports a crossed lacing system, Eastside Golf branding, a Wings logo on the tongue tag, and a linear pattern on the sole.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Eastside Golf Out of the Mud debuted on November 12th, 2022 for $130 retail.

product name: Jordan 1 Retro High Tokyo Bio Hack
product desp:
Remember back in 2005 when Nike collaborated on a Dunk High with Undefeated? The LA sneaker boutique put their very unique spin on the basketball silhouette, adding bold colors and an unpadded throat of the shoe. Now, the same mismatched color pattern has returned, only this time it on the Air Jordan 1.

The Air Jordan 1 Bio Hack pushes the model to a whole new territory when it comes to color palettes. The upper is made of various suedes and leathers, matched with a hodgepodge of black, Baroque Brown, and Racer Pink. A metallic leather Swoosh is contrasted by a light green midsole to add even further appeal to the traditional model.

The Air Jordan 1 Bio Hack released in September of 2020 for $170.

Crafted from a breathable mesh and canvas upper, the Nike Air Max 270 Black White now features 270 degrees of visible Air for extra comfort. Drawing inspiration from the sleek Air Max 180, the Nike Air Max 270 Black White features a slip-in bootie construction to deliver a great fit. The sneaker boasts a Max Air unit with 270 degrees of air encapsulated in the heel. The sneaker utilizes lightweight and soft neoprene across the upper to ensure airflow to the foot.

The Nike Air Max 270 Black White was released in March 2018 at a retail price of $160.

product name: Nike SB Dunk Low Crushed D.C.
product desp:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Crushed DC comes in a mix of Olive Grey, Mantra Orange, and Rattan color scheme.

It boasts marbled Swoosh brandings on both sides of the sneaker with Dusty Brown suede overlays. Although the SB Dunk Low lettering is still present on the tongues, it has been replaced with the phrase "Crushed D.C." while name tag-inspired graphics are put on the insoles. The shoes are constructed of NikeGrind materials and have tinted outsoles to match the base's embellishments. A perforated toe cap and lacing system completes the design.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Crushed DC debuted on October 7th, 2022, and retailed at $110.

product name: Nike LD Waffle sacai Undercover Black Bright Citron
product desp:
The Nike LDWaffle sacai Undercover Black Bright Citron is constructed with a black nylon upper with white and Bright Citron leather, and tonal grey hairy suede overlays. In alignment with other LDWaffles, the tongues, overlays, and soles are doubled, carrying out sacai's reconstructive design aesthetic.

The Nike LDWaffle sacai Undercover Black Bright Citron released in October of 2021 and retailed for $170.

Make sure your head isn’t in the beam while trying to grab the Jordan 6 Retro Black Infrared (2019). This AJ6 come with a black upper, black midsole plus red accents, and a translucent sole. These sneakers released in February 2019 and retailed for $200. This silhouette is a must cop, so purchase them on StockX now.

product name: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 LV8 40th Anniversary Sail Malachite
product desp:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low 07 LV8 Sail Malachite is dressed in four major hues: metallic gold, white, sail, as well as malachite.

The upper part of this Low Air Force 1 model is made of tumbled leather material. The sidewalls of this shoe have a green Swoosh emblem. A ‘Nike Air’ branding in white is also visible on this sneaker’s heel. It also comes with a white lacing system that completes its look and AIR units in its soles for cushioning.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low 07 LV8 Sail Malachite made its debut on October 13th, 2022, with a retail price of $130.

The Nike TC 7900 Sail W features the iconic Nike swoosh logo on the side, in the same color as the rest of the shoe. The tip of the swoosh wraps around the heel, blending into the mesh fabric.

This durable and comfortable Nike TC 7900 Sail W features an off-white sole that has a tread ideal for sports or walking in more rugged terrain. The upper part of the shoe is made of the same off-white color and features several types of materials, including mesh, which allows for enhanced breathability.

Released in March 2021, the Nike TC 7900 Sail W had an initial starting retail price of $126.

product name: Nike Air Force 1 Low SP Undefeated Multi-Patent Total Orange
product desp:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Undefeated Multi Patent comes in contrasting colors and has a shiny finish.

The paneled upper, which is made of patent leather, is finished in a patchwork of colors, including blue, fuchsia, crimson, purple, and black. Branding includes a laser engraved Nike Air logo on the heel tab and UNDFTD lace dubrae in addition to an embroidered orange Swoosh. The lateral heel and sewn tongue tag feature the Five Strikes logo of Undefeated. The low top is reinforced by a translucent rubber outsole and is built on a white midsole with encapsulated Air-sole.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low Undefeated Multi Patent was released on December 9th, 2022, retailing at $160.

product name: Jordan 1 Elevate Low SE Silver Toe (Women's)
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Elevate Low SE Silver Toe W has become a celebrated addition to the women's catalog.

This low-top sneaker features a black leather upper with semi-reflective silver accents in the area around the Nike Swoosh and toe. The shoe also boasts a Jordan Wings logo stamped behind the ankle and a classic Jumpman emblem stamped on top of the tongue. Nike Air technology in the non-slip white rubber sole along with stitching details around the top of the midsole complete the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Elevate Low SE Silver Toe W was released on October 19th, 2022, at a retail price of $130.

product colour: Color of the Month University Blue

product name: Nike Air Force 1 Low SP AMBUSH Game Royal
product desp:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low SP AMBUSH Game Royal is a collaborative sneaker in a dual color scheme.

It features a Royal Blue color both on the upper and the sole unit. It also displays extended Swooshes and pull tabs in a deep yellow shade. The branding "AMBUSH" sticks out from the support frame covering the lower part of the heel. A round perforated toe cap plus a co-branding tag at the tongue, a 3D printed "AF 1" lace tag, and protruding AIR branding are included in this design. The rubber sole has a linear pattern. 

The Nike Air Force 1 Low SP AMBUSH Game Royal debuted on December 16th, 2022, retailing at $190.

product name: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.02 Rookie Of The Year
product desp:
The Puma LaMelo Ball MB02 Rookie Of The Year is a collaborative sneaker between the iconic lifestyle brand and this rising star in the NBA.

Inspired by the Buzz City colorway, the Rookie of the Year version features a Blue Atoll woven mesh upper sporting LaMelo’s signature wings in Ultra Blue and White. Atoll Blue also comprises the foam-infused NITRO midsole, TPU heel clip, and rubber outsole, while the player´s branding on the tongue and heel, and "RARE" on the outsole are Ultra Blue. ROTY branding appears at the bottom of the laces and on the midsole.

The Puma LaMelo Ball MB02 Rookie Of The Year debuted on December 9th, 2022 for $130 retail.

product name: Nike Dunk High Retro Reverse Goldenrod

product desp:
The well-known Dunk High silhouette is given a neutral color tone by the Nike Dunk High Panda GS 2021. This sneaker features a combination of white, black and university red color scheme.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Starfish released in August of 2021 and retailed for $130.

There are red leather overlays on the shoe's upper part and a white midsole atop a red outsole finish its look. The signature Air Jordan's Wings emblem is found on the right upper side, with a similar emblem featuring on the left upper side of the left. This release pays homage to the first Jordan that Virgil ever owned, the Air Jordan 5. In signature fashion, Virgil has reimagined this classic silhouette in a way that embraces the importance of Nike Air technology. 

This Jordan 5 is comprised of a sail textile mesh upper with translucent netted panels and circular window inserts throughout the shoe. 3M reflective tongues, fire red Jordan branding, and an aged translucent outsole completes the design. These sneakers released in 2020 and retailed for $225.

Nike opened a new chapter at the end of 2020 and refreshed the Kobe 6 design with the Nike Kobe 6 Protro Grinch. The Kobe 6 Grinch originally debuted in 2011 when Kobe Bryant’s Los Angeles Lakers faced LeBron James’ Miami Heat in a legendary match up on Christmas Day. This is the first Kobe 6 to receive the Kobe Protro treatment, a design process that takes classic Kobe designs and updates them with modern tech for improved performance.

At a first glance, the Nike Kobe 6 Grinch looks identically like the OG pair from 2011: it features a Green Apple and Volt textured, snake-inspired upper as a tribute to Kobe’s Black Mamba moniker. A black Swoosh, red Kobe branding on the tongue, and green translucent outsole accentuate the shoe’s reptile theme. But, because this is a Protro, there are some differences. The updated Kobe 6 Grinch arrives with a more responsive Zoom Air cushioning system and scaled-down traction for an improved court feel. The silhouette shape is even altered to provide a lower, sleeker fit.

The Nike Kobe 6 Grinch released in December of 2020 and retailed for $180.

Its rubber outsole has a circular tread pattern for traction and durability.

The Nike SB Dunk Low HUF San Francisco is a collaborative sneaker made of a tumbled leather upper.

The upper has a white base that goes along with black overlays. Printed on the toe vamp of the shoe is a "HUF" text with a metallic Swoosh passing across it. Additional branding details include the standard Nike SB tongue imprint, texts reading "FOREVER" and "KEITH" on the right and left of the heel, respectively, and a reflective sky sill of the San Francisco city at the rear. A hidden tie-dye pattern is also found in white and orange.

The Nike SB Dunk Low HUF San Francisco debuted on November 16th, 2022, and retailed at $130.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Taxi was originally created by designer Peter Moore in 1985.
​
​The Air Jordan 1 is a color-block mix of Taxi yellow, black, and white, bringing out the aesthetic property of this footwear. The sneaker features yellow and black overlays with white leather uppers. The uniqueness of this silhouette is in the black midfoot Swooshes, the black laces, matching nylon tongues with Jumpman motifs, embroidered Wings rear motifs, and printed insoles. The white midsoles contrasting with yellow rubber outsoles complete the look. The shoe has ankle protection for maximum support and comfort.​
​
​The Air Jordan 1 Mid Taxi was released in September 2022 retailing at $125.

The Jordan 1 Low UNC 2021 arrives with a white leather upper with University Blue overlays and a black Swoosh. From there, a black Wings logo on the heel and a black woven tongue completes the design.

The Jordan 1 Low UNC 2021 released in July of 2021 and retailed for $90.

product name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Pearl
product desp:
Trailing the 2021 releases of the Ash Blue and Ash Stone colorways, Yeezy extended the Ash theme with the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Pearl. The Ash Pearl colorway builds off of previous models, utilizing material selection to create a stylish and responsive design.

Similar to the Ash Blue and Ash Stone releases, the upper of the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Pearl features a two-tone construction. White and black Primeknit make up the lower portion of the upper, while cream and tan make up the upper half. Dividing the two sections of the upper is a tan mesh stripe that runs across the lateral side of the shoe. A white and gum Boost sole adds the cushioning and responsiveness that the 350 is known for.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Pearl released in March of 2021 and retailed for $220.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Edge Glow (GS) for grade schoolers introduces some color to Michael Jordan’s signature shoe that has been re-engineered in youth sizing.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Edge Glow (GS) for grade schoolers is constructed on a white leather base covering the perforated toe and mid-panel. Highlighter pink, neon green, and orange piping introduce contrast, breaking up the neutral appearance between each panel. A Hyper Crimson leather Swoosh with pink trim appears on either side, while the Win(GS) for grade schoolers detailing is done in white on the collar. Underfoot, a white midsole and pink outsole finish off the look.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Edge Glow (GS) for grade schoolers was released in July 2020 and retailed for $100.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Triple White GS is a relatively simple Grade School–sized (GS) shoe with an all-white colorway. Constructed using tumbled leather, this Air Jordan Mid has precise tonal stitching, white Nike Swooshes, and a perforated toe box to increase breathability. The shoe’s upper sits atop a rubber outsole hardened to improve grip, with an Air-cushioned midsole to enhance comfort.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Triple White GS was released in 2020 as part of the Air Jordan collection. At the time of its release on June 30, 2020, this shoe had a retail price of $90.

product name: Jordan 1 Low SE Craft Obsidian French Blue Ashen Slate White
product colour: Obsidian French Blue Ashen Slate White
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Low SE Craft Obsidian French Blue Ashen Slate White arrives in a mixture of four main colors: obsidian, French blue, shen slate, and white.

The upper part of this Special Edition (SE) Low Air Jordan 1 sneaker is crafted from 100 percent leather. This shoe also comes with a "Wings" logo that is stamped on the heel, a stitched-down Swoosh logo, as well as a Jumpman Air design on its tongue. A perforated toe box and a linear pattern sole complete the look of this mid-profile model.

The Air Jordan 1 Low SE Craft Obsidian French Blue Ashen Slate White was released on November 8th, 2022, with a retail price of $120.

The Nike PG 6 Painted Swoosh is a multicolored basketball shoe designed by Tony Hardman.

The mesh upper of the PG 6 Painted Swoosh by Nike is a mix of color blots, creating an abstract mosaic of pink, blue, and citrus orange. The rest of the shoe is color blocked with a similar palette. The brush-stroked logos appear on both the lateral and medial sides of the shoe, with additional colors trickling out, creating a more prominent logo displayed on the sneaker. The white outsole rounds of the design.

The Nike PG 6 Painted Swoosh was first released in August 2022 at a retail price of $120.

While originally designed for more powerful runners, the Nike Air Max 95 Dark Beetroot sneaker, and brainchild of Sergio Lozano.

The Nike Air Max 95 Dark Beetroot silhouette boasts a black-to-grey gradient on the upper, black and white mesh panel eye stays, and burgundy-colored lace loops. To complete the anatomy-inspired aesthetic are mini Swoosh embroideries on the heel, "Air Max" labeling on the tongue, and an air bubble on the midsoles. It has dark burgundy hit with cutting-edge, anatomy-inspired aesthetics.

The Nike Air Max 95 Dark Beetroot sneaker was released in September 2022, retailing at $185.

Yeezy provided a new colorway of its most popular design with the adidas Yeezy 350 Flax, now available on StockX. This release shows slight resemblance to the 350 V2 Marsh in colorway, displaying warm tones to embody the arrival of spring. This model was released as a regional exclusive specific to the Asia Pacific and Africa.

This Yeezy 350 V2 Flax is composed of a light brown Primeknit upper with a translucent outer side stripe. A translucent Boost cushioned sole and light brown interior completes the design. These sneakers released in February of 2020 and retailed for $220.

After releasing the Nike Dunk Low Orange Pearl (W) and Nike Dunk Low College Navy (W) in the spring of 2021, Nike delivered yet another women’s exclusive Dunk Low this season with the Nike Dunk Low Green Glow (W). While the Green Glow is the first of its kind, its usage of traditional Dunk color blocking adds a familiarity to the design.

The upper of the Nike Dunk Low Green Glow (W) is composed of white leather with Green Glow leather overlays and Swoosh logos. From there, a woven Nike label is sewn to the tongue and a white "NIKE" is embroidered on the heel. A white midsole and Green Glow outsole completes the design.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Green Glow (W) released in April of 2021 and retailed for $100.

product name: Nike Dunk Low SE Teddy Bear Praline
product desp:
The Nike Dunk Low SE Teddy Bear Parline is dressed in a mixture of different color schemes, with pearl white, praline, hemp, as well as desert ocher coming as the principal colors.

This Special Edition (SE) Low Nike Dunk sneaker is constructed from a variety of materials and is decorated in tan and brown hues. A Nike tag on the side, as well as a teddy bear design on the medial heel, are prominent features of this shoe. The model is finished with a sail midsole sitting on a translucent gum outsole.

The Nike Dunk Low SE Teddy Bear Parline was made available on November 26th, 2022, with a retail price of $110.

The Jordan 3 Retro Black Cement Gold W, featuring black/grey elephant-designed overlays and a black leather upper, is an addition in the Women's catalog.

The sneaker features a metallic gold tone found at the ankle collar, around the eyelets, and at the tongue. The tongue, however, is accented with a red color that includes the Jumpman logo on it. Another emblem is displayed at the rear of the shoe. The sole unit comprises a lightly white-shaded midsole that sits on top of a grey outsole with a traction pattern.

The Jordan 3 Retro Black Cement Gold W was released on October 6th, 2022, and retailed at $200.

product name: Jordan 5 Retro Fire Red Silver Tongue (2020)
product desp:
Jordan remastered a 1990s masterpiece with the release of the Jordan 5 Retro Fire Red Silver Tongue (2020), now available on StockX. This is the fourth iteration of the original Fire Red colorway.

This Jordan 5 consists of a white leather upper with netted underlays and Fire Red detailing. A silver 3M reflective tongue with a red Jumpman logo, black and Fire Red midsole, and an icy translucent outsole completes the design. These sneakers released in March of 2020 and retailed for $200.

The Air Jordan 1 Low SE New Emerald was added to the Nike X Jordan brand collection. The primary hues are similar to the turbo green of 2019.

The footwear has unique color blocking and a rather diversified color palette. The sneaker is covered in bright white suede around the eye-stays, collar, toe, and heel, with a polished leather layer sitting underneath. The laces, lining, and underside of the tongue are light green, while the leather outsole and Jumpman logos are light gray with gold accents.

The Air Jordan 1 Low SE New Emerald was released on the market on July 14, 2022, and retailed at $130.

Yeezy adds another colorway of its most popular design with the adidas Yeezy 350 Cinder, now available on StockX. This 350 V2 stays true to Yeezy’s signature palette, sporting dark earth tones that provide a natural feeling.

This Yeezy 350 V2 is composed of a cinder Primeknit upper with a tonal side stripe. A cinder Boost cushioned midsole sole and gold outsole completes the design. These sneakers released in March of 2020 and retailed for $220.

The adidas Sambarose White Black Gum W was originally released in the 1950s. It has a gum outsole, as well as a suede T-toe panel. The sneaker model features a decorative zig-zag stitch progression and a softened leather construction.

The base of the Sambarose sneaker for women in White Black Gum is a bright white color and there are black details, including the three stripes that often appear on the sides of adidas shoes. There are also black details on the heel.

The adidas Sambarose White Black Gum W was first made available on the market in June of 2018. This model’s starting retail price was $100.

product name: New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Lunar New Year Dusty Lilac
product colour: Protection Pack Lunar New Year Dusty Lilac
product desp:
The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Dusty Lilac features a subtle pinkish-purple color inspired by the Lunar New Year.

The upper section of this 2002R Protection sneaker is a mauve mesh with leather overlays in dark purple and light gray and jagged suede overlays in dusty lilac. The laces are white, the insole is red, and the New Balance branding on the side panel is a dusty lilac outlined in purple and white. The midsole and heel cushioning are made of ABZORB and the outsole is constructed with N-ergy and Stability Web.

The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Dusty Lilac was released on December 30th, 2022 for a retail price of $170.

product name: New Balance 550 Lunar New Year Sea Salt
product desp:
The New Balance 550 Lunar New Year Cream was released as a special edition in a cream colorway.

This 550 sneaker’s upper has a smooth leather toe cap and heel, while perforated leather comprises the laterals of the upper, with some contrast arriving in the form of off-white and beige hues at the mid-foot, collar, and lower heel areas. Maroon appears on the New Balance branding on the top of the tongue and spine. A cream-colored midsole and a gray rubber outsole with a linear pattern finish off the design.

The New Balance 550 Lunar New Year Cream was released on December 30th, 2022, at a retail price of $130.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Rookie Season GS is an all-leather shoe with a white and university red color scheme for grade-schoolers (GS) that pays homage to the NBA´s team of Chicago Bulls team. 

The Swoosh and ankle flap are covered in glossy red patent panels. A jeweled, winged basketball logo with an iridescent finish is found on the panel. The quarter panels on both sides bear Michael Jordan's signature, and "CLUB: CHICAGO, 1984–85" is inscribed around the heel. The shoe also features a Nike Swoosh logo on its sides with a Jumpman logo printed on its tongue.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Rookie Season GS debuted on November 26th, 2022, and retailed at $120.

MSCHF’s Super Normal 2 "Common White" released January of 2023, and are the second iteration of MSCHF’s Super Normal silhouette. The new release of the sneaker has an updated sole tread and sidewall, which further extends their all-over liquified motif. The Common Whites are intended to be a daily wear shoe, deliberately released in quantity, and not intended for flipping, hence "Common." The shoes feature a full grain leather upper, and include an alternate tubular lace jewel.

product name: Nike Dunk High Retro PRM Faded Spruce
Nike Dunk Low Celestial Gold Suede (Women's)
Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Oil Green Orange

product desp:
The UGG Classic Ultra Mini Chestnut W, dressed in a Chestnut colorway, is a shoe for women.

The Classic Ultra Mini by Australian brand UGG features a Twinface sheepskin upper, a Suede heel counter with a rear pull tab, upcycled wool, a lyocell insole, a Foam footbed, and a Treadlite outsole. The sneaker’s design is completed by the textile binding that is made from recycled polyester fibers. The sneaker’s woven heel features a UGG labeled logo. Its outsole is trodden for traction.

The UGG Classic Ultra Mini Chestnut W was first made available on the 3rd of November, 2021. At the time, the retail price was set at $140.

product name: Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK White Black Metallic Silver
product desp:
The Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK White Black Metallic Silver is a thoughtfully crafted shoe. Notably, 40% of this sneaker is constructed from recycled materials. Its stretchy FlyKnit upper, for example, is made from recycled yarn.

Originally designed for running, this sneaker features a soft collar, webbing eyestays for a modern look, traditional lacing, and heel padding for comfort. It also features Nike Grind rubber details for increased traction and longevity and the VaporMax’s traditional TPU Clip. All these features are set atop its revolutionary VaporMax 2 Air unit.

The Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK White Black Metallic Silver was released in June 2021 at a retail price of $200.

The UGG Tasman Slipper Chestnut has become one of the most known colorways in the catalog and is constructed with wool fabric.

It has a foam footbed with a Treadlite outsole, as well as a Tasman braid that is stitched along the interior of the shoe, finishing the look after signature branding is stamped on the upper. Moreover, the footwear is waterproof and includes a detachable UGGplushTM sock made of recycled wool and TENCELTM Lyocell. The sole has the brand´s starburst pattern for traction.

The UGG Tasman Slipper Chestnut was released on the market on November 1st, 2021, and retailed at $100.

product name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Mystic Navy
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Low Mystic Navy arrives in a black and Mystic Blue smooth leather construction with identical color blocking and detailing to the original line of 1985 Air Jordan 1s. At the heel, a classic Jordan Wings logo nods to the silhouette's origins. From there, a white and Mystic Navy Air sole completes the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Mystic Navy released in June of 2022 and retailed for $130.

Composed of tonal grey mesh, suede, and leather, the adidas Yeezy 500 Granite offers a monochromatic styling similar to the early Yeezy 500s of 2018. Woven lace loops on the tongue nod to the tooling of 1990s hiking boots. From there, a sculptural sole with adiPrene cushioning provides comfort and support.

The adidas Yeezy 500 Granite released in May of 2022 and retailed for $210.

product name: New Balance 550 White Grey Dark Grey
product desp:
The New Balance 550 White Grey Dark Grey is a fresh take on the original 1989 design from this famous sneaker company.

The New Balance 550 White Grey Dark Grey features a dark grey hue around the heel, back of the ankle, and tongue. The tread underfoot, which was made with basketball in mind, has two different shades of grey that alternate. The midsoles are clean and simple, colored in a fresh white, and featuring the iconic "N" symbol that has come to be associated with New Balance. Perfect for both sports and walking around town, the New Balance 550 White Grey Dark Grey also has a breathable tongue to provide airflow.

First released in May 2022 at the retail price of $120.

The Nike Vaporwaffle sacai Black Gum features a black nylon upper with matching monochromatic suede overlays and tumbled leather Swooshes. Doubled tongues and Swooshes continue sacai's aesthetic of reconstruction and abstraction. At the base, a stacked foam midsole atop a gum outsole adds the finishing touch.

The Nike Vaporwaffle sacai Black Gum released in March of 2022 and retailed for $180.

The Nike Dunk Low 3D Swoosh features a smooth white leather upper with light grey overlays and a solid black Swoosh layered with hollow Swooshes in primary colors to depict three-dimensionality. From there, woven tongue labels and a foam sole complete the design.

The Nike Dunk Low 3D Swoosh released in May of 2022 and retailed for $100.

The Nike Dunk Low Graffiti Pink features mismatched right and left shoes, each with a canvas upper with a perforated toebox and a mottled pattern of pink, purple, green, black, and red.

The toe cap, eyestays, forefoot, and collar overlay of the same mottled canvas with frayed edging. The leather swoosh, laces, sock lining, and tongue tag with red Nike and swoosh are all black. There is also black Nike branding on one mostly green and one mostly purple heel tab. The insole is black with a white Nike and swoosh superimposed over a white "Pink." The midsole is white and the outsole is black.  

The Nike Dunk Low Graffiti Pink was released on May 1, 2022 for $110 retail.

product name: Nike Blazer Low sacai White Patent Leather
product desp:
The Nike Blazer Low sacai White Patent Leather refreshes sacai's signature Blazer Low with a glossy white patent leather construction. Doubled tongues, eyestays, and laces emphasize sacai's focus on reconstruction and abstract design. Finally, a stacked midsole provides an avant garde flair.

The Nike Blazer Low sacai White Patent Leather released in April of 2022 and retailed for $120.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Greyscale (GS) for grade schoolers has a gray tongue surrounded by black fabric.

This model features a bright white and bone-colored base made out of patches of leather. On top of this base, you will find patches of gray with purple hues, as well as pieces of black leather. The Nike Swoosh symbol is black and outlined with white stitching. The classic Air Jordan symbol appears in a light gray on the very top part of the tongue.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Greyscale (GS) for grade schoolers was first released in July of 2022. It had an initial retail price of $120.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro Military Black PS is a continuation of the coveted Air Jordan 4. Although this shoe is not an OG colorway, it borrows its composition of colors from the 1989 Air Jordan 4 Military Blue, simply swapping the iconic blue with black.

Like all other Air Jordan 4 retros, this modernized mid-top features mesh netting on the side panels and the tongue, a one-of-a-kind lacing support system that offers several eyelets for custom lace placement, supportive wings, and a rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro Military Black PS was released on 21st May 2022. Originally, it had a retail price of $90.

product name: Jordan 1 Low Craft Inside Out Black
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Low Inside Out Black, designed by Peter Moore, is a deconstruction of the White/Sail Inside Out Air Jordan 1 Low.

This is made of a mix of suede and leather with tonal black and grey hues in the different panels. The sneaker remixes the upper overlays into underlays while bringing out more detail in the leather toebox on top of the suede toecap. They have a retro vibe in the "Sail" and grey-sole piece with forthright single-stitched ‘23’ branding on the Swoosh and the Jordan branding on the shoe heel and tongue.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Inside Out Black was released in October 2022 with a retail price of $110.

The adidas Yeezy 500 Clay Brown presents an array of materials commonly found in hiking shoes designed to withstand the great outdoors. It is constructed of a Clay Brown mesh upper with leather and suede overlays that wrap the silhouette. A sturdy adiPRENE sole adds a responsive feel to the trail-ready design.

The adidas Yeezy 500 Clay Brown released in September of 2021 and retailed for $200.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Master (GS) for grade schoolers is convenient for both playing a game of basketball and casually walking around town. The shoes have the standard Nike high top tread.

This stylish model has a white base, with patches of leather in black and purple hues covering the body. Black laces lay on top of a black tongue, with the Air Jordan logo at the top of the tongue appearing in a shimmery pink shade.

The first release date of the Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Zen Master (GS) for grade schoolers was June 2022. The starting retail price for this model is $110.

The Air Jordan 14 Retro Ginger 2022 is the fourteenth signature release from the brand.

These Retro Ginger 2022 by Nike, from the tag Retro, are a relaunch of the popular original "OG" colorway Air Jordan 14. The sneaker is a mid-top model and features a golden upper and black and white highlights with the Jumpman logo on the outer part of both sides of the pair, the in-soles, the outer sole, and the back and front parts of the shoes.

The Air Jordan 14 Retro Ginger 2022 was released in August 2022 for a retail price of $210.

The adidas Yeezy 700 v3 Fade Salt features the silhouette’s signature glow-in-the-dark cage over a Fade Salt colorway.

The upper section of this collaborative V3 sneaker is made of Primeknit, with the RPU cage open at the forefoot to expose the tongue and laces. The inner section is constructed for a snug fit and the insole features both Yeezy and adidas branding. The thick, polyurethane midsole features full-length EVA cushioning and boasts adidas branding on its heel. The rubber outsole sports herringbone traction interspersed with pods. 

The adidas Yeezy 700 v3 Fade Salt originally debuted on September 22, 2022 for $210 retail.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Mummy draws inspiration from the Ancient Egyptian mummification process. It features a layered textile upper with cross-stitched detailing and a suede Swoosh overlay. At the heel, eye graphics peek out from underneath the layered textile. A glow-in-the-dark sole and Eye of Horus woven tongue tag completes this Halloween design.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Mummy released in October of 2021 and retailed for $110.

product name: Jordan 5 Retro DJ Khaled We The Best Sail
product colour: DJ Khaled We The Best Sail
product desp:
The Air Jordan 5 Retro DJ Khaled We The Best Sail comes toned in a mixture of three colors; violet star, washed yellow, and sail.

This collaborative Air Jordan 5 has an off-white leather upper. The shoe also has a quilting lining in powder blue and a midsole made of Violet Star Air-assisted Polyurethane. A vintage Jumpman emblem with the words "Keep Going" on the inside and a shiny silver polish on the outside decorates the tongue. On uneven heel overlays, the 'We the Best' branding and the Nike Air insignia are visible.

The Air Jordan 5 Retro DJ Khaled We The Best Sail retailed for $225 on its market debut in November 2022.

The Air Jordan 1 High Element Gore Tex Berry continues the food-themed colorways of the AJ1 and now features a waterproof GORE-TEX construction, durable nubuck leather, winter lining, and a gusseted tongue.

GORE-TEX is utilized for weatherproofing the Air Jordan 1 High Element Gore Tex Berry via a mix of ripstop, suede, and leather materials, while the heels bear the distinct GORE-TEX marking. Black accents are visible throughout the pair, and underfoot, a white midsole and a half black and grey translucent rubber outsole top off the design.

The Air Jordan 1 High Element Gore Tex Berry was released in March 2022 and originally retailed for $200.

product name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Mist
product desp:
The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Mono Mist's upper delivers monofilament mesh, a new material choice for the sneaker. Lastly, traditional Boost sole is added to the sole.

The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Mono Mist released in June of 2021 for $220, exclusively in EU.

Reimagining the original Air Jordan 12 Taxi, the Jordan 12 Retro Low Golf Taxi brings the renowned colorway from the hardwood to the fairways. In traditional fashion, it features a white tumbled leather paneled upper with textural black leather mudguards. At the base, a modified sole with deep grooves offers maximum traction and support.

The Jordan 12 Retro Low Golf Taxi released in March of 2022 and retailed for $220.

product name: Jordan 13 Retro Gym Red Flint Grey
product desp:
Jordan flipped one of the most popular Jordan 13 colorways of all time to create a new colorway with the Air Jordan 13 Red Flint. The Red Flint draws its inspiration from the often re-issued Air Jordan 13 Flint, remixing to the iconic colorway.

The Air Jordan 13 Red Flint features an upper made of red reflective mesh, white leather, and Flint Durabuck. In line with Jordan 13s of the past, a holographic Jumpman emblem is displayed on the lateral ankle. An embroidered Jumpman insignia on the tongue, and a Flint and white sole complete this Jordan 13.

The Jordan 13 Red Flint released in April of 2021 and retailed for $190.

To honor the 30th Anniversary of the Jordan 5, Jordan Brand added a "What The?" treatment to its catalog with the Jordan 5 What The. This design boasts a mix of materials and details from Jumpman’s best Non-OG Jordan 5 colorways, including the Tokyo, Shanghai, Raging Bull, Bel-Air, Laser, Green Bean, Olive, and Quai 54 colorways.

In true mismatched fashion, each foot of the Jordan 5 What The showcases a different look. On the right, yellow suede from the Tokyo 5 smothers the upper atop a purple and blue speckled Belair 5 midsole with a patterned interior pulled from the Jordan 5 Olive. On the left, red suede tributing the Raging Bull Jordan 5 covers the upper atop a black, grey, and lime green sole that references the Quai 54 iteration. Heel embroidery nodding to the Shanghai and Tokyo models, icy translucent outsoles, and 3M reflective tongues complete this scrambled iteration.

The Jordan 5 What The released in November of 2020 and retailed for $220.

The Nike Lebron 20 Miami Heat, available in different hues - including black, university red, university gold, and light smoke gray - is one of the collaborative designs between this iconic American brand and the NBA champion from Akron.

The upper section of the Lebron 20 model is made of black woven textile with a double Swoosh on its right side. The sneaker has an elongated tongue beneath the laces made from cotton. Its midsole and outsole, which are both made from rubber, appears in the black and red colors.

The Nike Lebron 20 Miami Heat was first released on October 24th, 2022 with $200 as the retail price.

Jordan Brand revisited a colorway from their Player Exclusive archive for the Air Jordan 6 Electric Green. The Electric Green is nearly identical to the Air Jordan 6 Oregon Ducks PE that surfaced in 2018.

The Air Jordan 6 Electric Green features an all-black Durabuck upper with hits of Electric Green on the heel tab, tongue, and midsole. A milky, green translucent outsole finishes off this retro model.

The Air Jordan 6 Electric Green released in June of 2021 and retailed for $190.

product name: Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70 Ox Comme des Garcons PLAY Black
product desp:
Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70s Ox Comme des Garcons PLAY Black is a model of the iconic collaboration between Comme des Garcons, a Japanese Brand, and Converse. Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70s Ox Comme des Garcons PLAY Black features a canvas upper. It also features contrasting lace colorways and white seams. On the side, it features the famous red heart and a silhouette that ends on the cream-colored sole.

Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70s Ox Comme des Garcons PLAY Black was released in July 2017 and had a retail price of $120.

Inspired by the Midnight Navy Air Jordan 1 CO. JP, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Bordeaux GS is one of the signature colorways that dropped as part of the Jordan Brand Fall 2021 lineup.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Bordeaux GS colorway features a white leather upper with Bordeaux overlays, a metallic silver Swoosh, and a jeweled Air Jordan Wings logo. It also features a woven Nike tag on its nylon tongue, a cushioned white midsole, and a sturdy Bordeaux rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Bordeaux GS was released in November 2021. It retailed at $130.

product name: Jordan 4 Retro SP 30th Anniversary Union Desert Moss
product desp:
The Air Jordan 4 Union LA Desert Moss features a Dark Iris mesh upper with Desert Moss suede overlays and translucent lace loops. From there, turquoise heel tabs and Union LA woven tabs on the lateral side complete the design.

The Air Jordan 4 Union LA Desert Moss released in June of 2021 and retailed for $225.

product name: Jordan 1 Retro High Light Army Rust Shadow Patina
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Patina features a black leather upper with Light Army suede and copper-finished leather overlays. A mint Nike Air logo patch is stitched atop a black nylon tongue, adding a hit of color to the otherwise earth tone colorway.

The Air Jordan 1 Patina released in May of 2021 and retailed for $170.

One of the most anticipated releases of 2018, the Air Jordan 3 Retro OG marked the first time original "Nike Air" branding was featured on the "Black Cement" AJ 3 since it's 2001 retro. Jordan stuck to the mantra of "if it aint broke, don’t fix it," on these, staying true to the OG with a black-based leather upper with cement grey, fire red, and white accents, finished off by the iconic elephant print detailing. Their release date was on Michael Jordan's 55th birthday, February 17th, 2018, and went for $200 in mens sizes. The "Black Cement" Air Jordan 3 Retro OG is a must-have, and you don't need us to tell you that. They should be in everyone's collection, multiples if possible. If you're on the hunt for a pair, you can buy them online today. Those with a pair to sell can hit up the StockX marketplace and see what they're currently going for.

product name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Black Phantom (TD)
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Black Phantom TD, designed for toddlers, is a collaborative sneaker between Nike and the American musician.

This Low Air Jordan 1 features a nubuck and suede upper in a black/phantom tone with contrast white stitching. The rapper’s trademark reverse Swoosh is visible on the lateral, with the normal facing Swoosh on the medial. A woven Nike tag on the tongue, Cactus Jack branding on the sock liner, mismatched heel tabs displaying the Wings logo, and a bee graphic, plus a black rubber cupsole complete the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Black Phantom TD was released on December 15th, 2022, retailing at $50.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Team Red is a mid-top sneaker dressed in a cherrywood red and gray color scheme.

This Air Jordan 1 features an all-leather upper with cherrywood overlays against the gray underlays. The color is also visible on the lining and laces. Branding details include Swooshes on the laterals and medials, the Air Jordan Wings logo on the ankle, and the Jumpman logo on the tongue tag and insole. Completing this shoe’s design is a white midsole that sits on a grey rubber outsole with AIR units.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Team Red was released on the 20th of August 2022, retailing at $125.

product name: Nike Air Force 1 Low 40th Anniversary Edition Bronx Origins

product desp:
The New Balance 990v3 Grey 2019 is one of the 2019 releases by shoe manufacturer New Balance.

The New Balance 990v3 Grey 2019 comes in grey and features a leather upper section. The upper part is also made of mesh patches in grey. In addition, the shoe has an ENCAP midsole cushioning with a lightweight foam combined with a rim made of durable polyurethane. The shoe also has white laces for a secure fit and the New Balance logo on both sides.

The New Balance 990v3 Grey 2019 was released on 1st October 2019 to retail at $165.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Bordeaux GS, made mostly out of leather material, has a pure white upper with dark red overlays and perforations found at its forefoot.

The white nylon tongue of this Air Jordan 1 for grade-schoolers (GS) is embroidered with a metallic silver Jumpman logo. Other brand aspects include the mid-foot Swooshes with a dark red - cherrywood red - matte look and printed wing motifs on the insoles and at the back of the shoes. Finishing up the look is a white midsole that comes along with a burgundy outsole and AIR units for cushioning.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Bordeaux GS debuted on November 15th, 2022, retailing at a price of $110.

The Air Jordan 1 Low White Toe features the team colors of the NBA's Chicago Bulls. 

  White leather was used to design the perforated toe box. Except for the Fire Red leather Swoosh, the upper's remaining portions are covered in Black leather. On the heel, there is a stitched "Wings" emblem, while the tongue's black nylon is stitched with a red Jumpman. A black rubber outsole with a linear pattern for traction and a white midsole round out the shoe.

The Air Jordan 1 Low White Toe debuted on the market on October 11th, 2022. It initially retailed at the price of $110.

product name: Nike Air Max BW OG Persian Violet (2021)
product desp:
In celebration of its 30th Anniversary, Nike reissued the original 1991 Air Max BW with the Nike Air Max BW Persian Violet.

One of the lesser-known designs from legendary Nike and Jordan designer Tinker Hatfield, the Nike Air Max BW introduced a larger visible Air Unit to the Air Max line, which led to the name Big Window (BW for short). In addition to enhanced visible Air, the design boasts a layered construction of black and white mesh, leather, and Durabuck with blue Swooshes.

The Nike Air Max BW Persian Violet released in September of 2021 and retailed for $130.

The Nike Air Zoom Alphafly NEXT Flyknit Hyper Violet has become a celebrated addition to the brand´s running catalog.

This Alphafly Nike Zoom comes in a mix of hyper violet, crimson, and black shades with a large Swoosh on its laterals. It features two slimline Zoom Air Units toward the forefoot, for responsiveness. At the midsole, the shoe has a carbon fiber plate, which propels each step. Its FlyKnit upper is steamed and stretched to offer a contoured fit enhancing and water absorption.

The Nike Air Zoom Alphafly NEXT Flyknit Hyper Violet was released on March 17th, 2022, at a retail price of $275.

product name: Nike Air Force 1 '07 Low Color of the Month University Red Gum
product colour: Color of the Month University Red Gum
product desp:
The Nike Air Force 1 07 Low Color of the Month University Red Gum is footwear inspired by the 1984 "Color of the Month" series.

The Air Force 1 07 Low in Red Gum by Nike has a white leather upper with a red signature Swoosh on the side. The woven Nike tongue has crimson accents matching the Nike Air embroidery on the shoe heel. The cup soles are made of rubber for more durability. The sneaker comes with a shoe-cleaning toothbrush with "Since 1982" branding.

The Nike Air Force 1 07 Low Color of the Month University Red Gum was released in August 2022 at a retail price of $150.

New Balance 550 White Natural Indigo Burgundy
Nike Air Force 1 Low SP AMBUSH Pine Green
product desp:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low SP AMBUSH Pine Green, designed by Yoon Ahn, was part of a special collaboration between fashion designer Ahn and Nike.

The sneaker features a textured upper of pine green leather. The shoe also has a matching rubber outsole with AIR cushioning. Variable-width lacing and perforations on the toebox are accented by a TPU heel clip. The signature Swoosh is elongated and appears in a citron - pale yellow - hue that is repeated on the lace dubrae, tongue tag, and heel tab in a leather material.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low SP AMBUSH Pine Green was released on December 16th, 2022, at a retail price of $190.
