product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Mid Diamond Shorts for Grade School sizing (GS) is a Jordan brand colorway with a white and black scheme. Designed to honor the iconic Diamond Jordan basketball shorts, this mid-top sneaker features a white leather upper with black suede overlays on its eyelets, collar, and toe area. Additionally, it features nylon tongues, suede Nike Swooshes on its side panels, stamped wings logos on its collars, a rubber midsole, and a rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Diamond Shorts GS was released on 9th February 2022. During its release, it had a retail price of $100.

product name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Rock
product desp:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Rock features a marbled black, grey, and brown Primeknit upper styled in a pattern similar to the Yeezy 350 V2 MX Oat, only with dark tones. In signature fashion, a cushioned Boost sole, heel tab, and mesh side stripe complete the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Rock released in December of 2021 and retailed for $220.

The Nike Dunk Low Reverse Panda features the Nike Swoosh logo in black on the tongue and also on the heel padding behind the ankle.

The Nike Dunk Low Reverse Panda has a clean white color throughout, including the sole, with contrasting touches of black. The shoe also features a lace-up closure style with black laces. The Nike Swoosh is found on both sides, also in black, and these meet behind the ankle and below the white heel padding.

The Nike Dunk Low Reverse Panda first debuted in Asia in June, 2022, and then in the UK and Europe in July of 2022 at a retail price of $100.

Similar to the original Air Jordan 4 Retro Lightning, the 2021 Grade School edition features a mid-top with a bright yellow nubuck upper. The yellow nubuck upper boasts black molded eyelets and matching black netting. In addition to its impressive mid-top, the Air Jordan 4 Retro Lightning 2021 GS also features a molded Jumpman logo as well as dark grey accents on its wings, a white foam midsole, and a grey rubber outsole.

This magnificent colorway, which was released in August 2021, currently retails at $150.

product name: Nike Air Trainer 1 SP Travis Scott Wheat
product desp:
Drawing inspiration from hiking culture and gear, the Nike Air Trainer 1 SP Travis Scott Grey Wheat arrives in a dark brown canvas construction with matching mesh overlays and single stitch Swoosh logos. Canvas shrouds on the upper give wearers options for styling. At the heel and inside of the tongue, concealed zipper pockets provide extra storage. From there, "Cactus Corporation" insignias at the heel and forefoot velcro strap complete the design.

The Nike Air Trainer 1 SP Travis Scott Wheat released in May of 2022 and retailed for $160.

The adidas Yeezy 450 Utility Black is made of synthetic fibers, a product of a combination of petroleum-based ethylene-vinyl acetate and foam from algae.

The design of adidas Yeez 450 Utility Black is renowned for its comfortable, tight, sock-like fit as well as its fashionable mesh style. The shoe has a semitranslucent rubber outsole and thermoplastic polyurethane (TPU) for performance and flexibility. The design of adidas Yeezy 450 comes in Utility Black.

adidas Yeezy 450 Utility Black was released on February 8, 2022 at a retail price of $200.

product name: Nike Killshot 2 J Crew Sail Midnight Navy
product desp:
In 2017, the re-release of the Nike Killshot 2 J Crew Sail Midnight Navy marked the return of one of Nike's most popular exclusives. The history of the Killshot goes all the way back to the 1970s, but Nike launched the Midnight Navy colorway in 2012 as part of its collaboration with J.Crew. Originally, the Nike Killshot 2 J Crew Sail Midnight Navy was exclusively available at J.Crew. However, Nike re-released the Midnight Navy five year later globally.

The Nike Killshot 2 J Crew Sail Midnight Navy features a retro design that's reminiscent of Nike's original shoes from the 1970s. The shoe starts with a thick tan sole with an aged, weathered appearance and then leads to a clean, off-white upper with gray accents and a navy Swoosh logo. Instead of rubber, the Nike Killshot 2 J Crew Sail Midnight Navy comes with a gum sole with a textured underside to complete the retro look. For a final touch, "NIKE" is printed on the heel in weathered navy letters to suggest that this sneaker has seen a lot of history.

The Nike Killshot 2 J Crew Sail Midnight Navy released in February of 2017 and retailed for $90.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Vermillion features an all-red one piece EVA foam construction with oval cut-outs to provide ventilation. At the base, a cushioned footbed offers support and stability.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Vermillion released in October of 2021 and retailed for $80.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Banned (2020) takes the classic Banned colorway of the high-top Jordan 1 and applies it to the mid-cut sneaker.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Banned (2020) features full-grain black and red leather uppers. Similar to the original Air Jordan 1 Banned, hits of red leather on the toe, collar, heel, and Swoosh. The only difference from the original Banned colorway is the red leather around the eyelets.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Banned (2020) released in November 2021 for $110.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Tie Dye features the eye-catching "Black Toe" formula and is accented with a tie-dye pattern on the heel.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Tie Dye features a white leather base adopting the "Black Toe" color blocking on the toe boxes, tongues, and eyelets. Besides the white and black color scheme, the silhouette offers tie-dye graphics on the upper ankle and heel areas. Moreover, the pair includes traditional Jordan branding on the tongue and heel. Underfoot, the upper rests atop a mint and white sole unit.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Tie Dye was released as part of the Spring 2022 collection and retailed for $110.

The New Balance 550 White Grey GS shoe was originally designed by Aimé Leon Dore in 1989, and this model is by Teddy Santis.

The 550 White Grey for grade-schoolers has a smaller size release with smaller price tags. The 80’s-era and vintage look sneakers feature an anti-skid grey outsole and white uppers made of smooth leather. They feature the 550 New Balance branding on the front lace, New Balance logo on the tongue, and a large N logo on the lateral and medial sidewalls.

The New Balance 550 White Grey GS Grade School shoe was released in July 2022 and retaialed for $80.

product name: Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves White
product desp:
The Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves White is a sneaker that was released as a collaboration between Nike and Patta as a commemorative the 1-of-1 "ROMAN FOREVER" iteration, remembering Patta co-founder Edson Sabjo’s late son.

The White Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves has a mix of white leather and blue-tinted grey mesh that features a distinct wavy leather overlay above cream-colored Air bubble midsoles. Logos of "Patta Air Max" are found on the tongue tabs and the insoles are blank. Nike Air emblems round out the design on the heel and white waffle outsoles. 

The sneaker was released on the 26th of August, 2022, with a retail price of $160.

product name: Jordan 1 Mid SE Pastel Vivid Green Grind (GS)
product desp:
The model known as the Air Jordan 1 Mid Pastel Grind (GS) has a sole with a thin strip of transparent plastic that contains sparkles, with a strip of white on top.

The upper body of the shoe is made out of different types of canvas, including patches of white, pink, yellow, and gold. The Air Jordan 1 Mid Pastel Grind (GS) for grade schoolers is a high-top model, so you can expect it to hit the top of the average wearer’s ankle. It’s designed for use on and off the basketball court.

First released in March of 2022, the Air Jordan 1 Mid Pastel Grind (GS) for grade schoolers had a retail price starting at $110.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Alternate Bred Toe W, designed by Peter Moore, highlights the Chicago-inspired palette design.
​
This women's Air Jordan 1 has a trio of colors with black, white, and red. It blends the bright white midsoles and mid panels, the black leather overlays, collars, toe boxes, and rich red Checks. The shoe has red outsoles and liners with the black branding on the tongue rounding out this shoe design. The tongue tag is decorated with a woven Jumpman. The sneaker mid-top is a rubber cup-sole mounted with Air-sole cushioning in the shoe heel for added comfort.
​
​The Air Jordan 1 Mid Alternate Bred Toe W was launched in July 2022 at a retail price of $110.

product name: Jordan 1 Low SE Light Smoke Grey Gym Red
product desp:
The Jordan 1 Low Light Smoke Grey Gym Red features a smooth white leather upper with grey Durabuck overlays and red leather Swooshes and collars. At the heel, an embroidered Jordan Wings logo pays homage to the original Air Jordan logo. From there, a matching sole completes the design.

The Jordan 1 Low Light Smoke Grey Gym Red released in November of 2021 and retailed for $100.

If you are looking for a very unique pair of Jordans then the Air Jordan 1 Low Noble Green GS shoes are just for you.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Noble Green GS offers a green and white sole with a green, black, and white accent on the shoe. The tongue and laces are black and the back of the shoe offers the Air Jordan logo in a white stencil. What stands out the most is the Jumpman logo in striking gold on the top of the shoe's tongue.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Noble Green GS had their release in October 2021 and retailed at $85.

The Nike Dunk Low Magma Orange W appears in a magma orange colorway in the women´s (W) catalog.

The upper of this Low Nike Dunk model is made of soft and premium leather with its tongue featuring faded graphics. The pearl white perforated toe cap and organic cotton laces complete the retro design of this sneaker. The white midsole and magma orange colored outsole are made of rubber. They include cushioning technology. The design is completed by Swoosh emblems.

The Nike Dunk Low Magma Orange W was made available for the first time on September 27th, 2022, at a retail price of $120.

product name: Jordan 2 Retro SP Maison Chateau Rouge
product desp:
In collaboration with Paris-based boutique and fashion label Maison Château Rouge, the Air Jordan 2 Maison Château Rouge celebrates global youth culture with its playful palette and unique detailing. It features an off-white leather upper with textural overlays, light grey suede mud guards, and orange suede toe and heel wraps. From there, brogue-style perforations and zig-zagged eyestays add a luxurious feel, while hand-stitched detailing channels a DIY element.

The Air Jordan 2 Maison Château Rouge released in July of 2022 and retailed for $225.

The Jordan 1 Mid Grey Green features a white leather upper with grey Durabuck overlays and metallic green Swooshes and collars. From there, a metallic green lace tag and signature Wings logo on the collar completes the design.

The Jordan 1 Mid Grey Green released in November of 2021 and retailed for $120.

With a simplified two-piece construction, the adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate features Dark Slate foam sole that clasps a monochromatic sock-like Primeknit upper. From there, thick rope laces add the finishing touches.

The adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate released in June of 2021 and retailed for $200.

The Nike Air Max 2013 Stüssy Fossil boasts a netted mesh upper with woven overlays, frayed textile side Swooshes, and Stüssy branding at the forefoot - - nodding to past Air Zoom Spiridon and Air Force 1 collaborations. Taking a vintage approach, aged-looking, clouded Air units at the base complete the design.

The Nike Air Max 2013 Stüssy Fossil released in August of 2022 and retailed for $210.

product name: Nike LD Waffle sacai CLOT Kiss of Death Net Orange Blaze
product colour: sacai CLOT Kiss of Death Net Orange Blaze
product desp:
Taking cues from the Nike Air Max 1 CLOT Kiss of Death, the Nike LDWaffle sacai CLOT Orange Blaze boasts an off-white translucent and suede upper with Deep Red and Orange Blaze snake-textured Swooshes. From there, a two-toned stacked sole and doubled tongue amplify sacai's unique design aesthetic.

The Nike LDWaffle sacai CLOT Orange Blaze released in September of 2021 and retailed for $170.

product name: Nike Air Force 1 Shadow Triple White (W)
product desp:
The women's Nike Air Force 1 Shadow Triple White (W) features a reconstructed white leather upper with monotone Swooshes and overlays. At the base, a thick white Air sole completes the design.

The women's Nike Air Force 1 Shadow Triple White (W) released in October of 2019 and retailed for $120.

product name: Nike LD Waffle sacai CLOT Kiss of Death 2 Cool Grey
product colour: sacai CLOT Kiss of Death 2 Cool Grey
product desp:
The Nike LDWaffle sacai CLOT Cool Grey features a tonal grey mesh upper with dual tongues and 3M Swooshes. Each Swoosh is thin and reinforced with a heat-pressing technique, similar to Hyperfuse technology. A stacked midsole and gum outsole complete the design.

The Nike LDWaffle sacai CLOT Cool Grey was released in October of 2021 and retailed for $180.

product name: Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf Triple White
product desp:
The Jordan 1 Low Golf Triple White features a white tumbled leather upper with matching overlays and Swooshes. A debossed Wings logo at the heel nods to the first-ever Air Jordan logo that debuted in 1985. At the base, a grooved outsole provides support, no matter where you are on the golf course.

The Jordan 1 Low Golf Triple White released in January of 2022 and retailed for $140.

product name: Jordan 1 Low Black Dark Powder Blue (Women's)
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Low White Black Dark Powder Blue W for women joined the OG-styled Jordan 1 Low brand.

Expressing a mix of white, black, and dark powder blue colors, this Air Jordan 1 Low features a white base. The black color appears on the overlay panels, shoe laces, and the tongue. The dark powder blue accents appear on the outsole, heel counter, and tongue tags. The design is completed by the white perforated toe box, white midsole, and a black Swoosh. The outsole is further traded for traction.

The Air Jordan 1 Low White Black Dark Powder Blue W was released in July 2022 with a retail price set at $120.

First appearing on PGA Tour pro Pat Perez back in July of 2021, the Jordan 4 Golf Bred offers tribute to one of the most renowned OG Air Jordan 4 colorways to ever release, the Air Jordan 4 Bred. Its upper practically mimics the original design, not including the classic Nike Air logo heel tab where a Jumpman logo is featured instead. Tailoring the design for the greens, spikes on the outsole offer stability and traction for that perfect swing.

The Air Jordan 4 Golf Bred released in December of 2021 and retailed for $220.

product name: Nike Dunk Low Essential Paisley Pack Green (Women's)
product desp:
The Nike Dunk Low Essential Paisley Pack Green W is part of the Dunk Low Paisley Pack released by Nike Sportswear for 2022.

This version of the Nike Dunk Low features a white leather base with green leather overlays, laces, insoles, rubber outsole, and nylon tongues. Its most notable features are its bandana print swoosh logos and heel tabs. For increased grip, this sneaker features designed patterns beneath its outsole, whereas it features a perforated toe box to increase its breathability.

The Nike Dunk Low Essential Paisley Pack Green W was released on 10th March 2022 at a retail price of $120.

product name: New Balance 550 Aime Leon Dore White Leather
product desp:
The New Balance 550 Aime Leon Dore White Leather is dressed in an all-white color scheme.

This collaborative sneaker has a leather base. The toe box of the shoe is cream, and it has white as well as light grey overlays throughout. In addition to the ALD as well as the New Balance co-branding on the tongue tag, the "N" logo and heel overlay are also visible on this model in grey textured suede. The rubber midsole features cream, while the outsole of the shoe is rubber.

The New Balance 550 Aime Leon Dore White Leather first launched on November 2nd, 2022, with a retail price set at $130.

product name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Retro QS West Indies (2022)
model: Nike Air Force 1 Low Retro QS
product desp:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Retro QS West Indies 2022, designed by Bruce Kilgore, celebrates its 20th anniversary in a white-classic green colorway.
​
The QS West Indies 2022 Air Force 1 by Nike has a white leather upper highlighted with classic green accents on the heel tab and collar lining. The shoe tongue tag is woven with the West Indies branding. The shoe has an embroidered "West Indies" and palm tree on the lateral heel. For comfort, the sneaker has durable rubber cupsoles paired with white sidewalls and a green rubber outsole.
​
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Retro QS West Indies 2022 was launched in August 2022, retailing at $140.

product name: Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT 25 Years In China
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT 25 Years In China features a mixture of three main hues: pink, grey, and royal blue.

This anniversary Zoom Air Jordan 1 pays homage to the brand´s presence in the country. It has a strong white background with colorful overlays that resemble brush strokes on the cutout Swoosh emblems as well as on the collars. This model also features the signature Air Jordan Wings Emblem in a royal blue hue. A white midsole that tops a blue outsole completes the look.

The Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT 25 Years In China retailed for $150 on its market debut in September 2022.

product name: Jordan 1 Retro High NC to Chi Leather (W)
product desp:
Jordan Brand revisits the silhouette that started it all with the women's Jordan 1 Retro High NC to Chi Leather (W), now available on StockX. This shoe pays homage to MJ’s journey to the NBA, starting as a phenom at UNC to becoming one of the greatest of all time and winning 6 championships as a Chicago Bull.

This women's Jordan 1 is composed of a black tumbled leather upper with red and university blue overlays. A white midsole, red outsole, and classic Nike branding on the tongue complete the design. These sneakers released in February of 2020 and retailed for $170.

product name: Nike Kobe 5 Protro Undefeated Hall of Fame
product desp:
The Nike Kobe 5 Protro Undefeated Hall of Fame arrives in gold, purple, and black, a colorway that pays homage to the Mamba and his Lakers legacy. The Nike Kobe 5 Protro Undefeated Hall of Fame features a gold-colored, textured upper with mesh toe boxes and side paneling. Snakeskin-textured overlays add nuance on the tops, and each shoe is accented with a purple Swoosh on the right side panel and pink Swoosh on the left, with the numbers 24, 10, and 8 inscribed on the pink Swoosh. Below, Zoom Air provides additional cushioning.

The Nike Kobe 5 Protro Undefeated Hall of Fame was released in May, 2021, at a retail price of $190.

product name: Nike Air VaporMax Plus Triple Red
product desp:
Nike offers cushioning, comfort, and style with the Nike Air VaporMax Plus Triple Red.

The Nike Air VaporMax Plus triple red features TPU overlays along the upper of the midfoot. The shoe also incorporates neoprene mesh all over the shoe. Its well-padded upper complements the VaporMax Air midsole. The model is entirely draped in Red and neoprene hells, branding, and midsole. The Nike Air VaporMax Plus triple red also features a full-length VaporMax Sole unit with the signature "VM" branding on the heels and the insoles.

The Nike Air VaporMax Plus Triple Red was launched on the 14th of February, 2020 at a retail price of $190.

product name: Nike Zoom Cortez SP sacai Iron Grey
product desp:
The Nike Cortez 40 sacai Grey features a mixture of different colors, with white, dark grey, and iron grey being the three most dominant tones.

The collar and the heel counter on these Nike Cortez 40s sneakers have a stacked-on appearance. Co-branding is visible on the leather heel tab. The design of the shoe is completed with a midsole with layers of sail as well as a grey and herringbone-patterned charcoal grey rubber outsole.

The Nike Cortez 40 sacai Grey was released to the market on December 13th, 2022 with $180 as the initial retail price.

Since its release, Nike Air Max 95 NH Ironstone Celery continues to be one of the variants of Nike’s Air Max 95 series, recording the highest number of sales.

The upper of the shoe comprises a mixture of different materials, which replaces the suede and mesh construction from which the original Nike Air Max 95 was made. The lace loops of the shoe have netting that come in different shades of grey and black. Brown make-ups are also visible across the upper with much of the sole being black.

Nike Air Max 95 NH Ironstone Celery debuted on February 9, 2022. The release price of the shoe by then was $185.

product name: adidas Samba Classic Black White Dark Gum
product desp:
The adidas Samba Classic Black White Dark Gum is a classic sneaker and streetwear staple.​
​​
​The Classic adidas Samba is made from premium leather and comes in a black-and-white colorway. The sneakers have the iconic serrated 3-Stripes that identify the brand, as well as the gold "Samba" and the adidas logo on the foldable tongue. It has black laces and a black gum sole. The shoe has a suede toe overlay and a woven "SAMBA" tongue label.​
​
​The adidas Samba Classic Black White Dark Gum was released on June 1, 2022, for a retail price of $70.

After a slew of collaborative releases with adidas and Nike, DC-based sneaker boutique A Ma Maniére teamed up with Jordan Brand to release a women’s exclusive Jordan 3 with the Air Jordan 3 A Ma Maniére (W). The release aligns with their short film Raised By Women, an ode to the strides and accomplishments of everyday women in urban communities.

The Air Jordan 3 A Ma Maniére arrives featuring a white tumbled leather upper with Medium Grey suede on the toe wrap, eyestay, heel wrap, and ankle. Each panel of leather on the upper has a raw trim, revealing a natural, tan edge. To provide a vintage aesthetic, the eyelets, heel tab, and lower portion of the midsole are yellowed. From there, the tongue on the left sneaker features an embroidered A Ma Maniére logo, while the right features a Jumpman logo. Quilted satin lining on the interior of the shoe adds an element of luxury. A white, Violet Ore, and Medium Grey sole with a classic Air unit in the heel completes this retro look.

The women's Air Jordan 3 A Ma Maniére released in April of 2021 and retailed for $200.

Please Note: The clear heel tab does experience slight yellowing due to storage by the manufacturer. The Air Jordan 3 Fragment is the follow up to the very popular 2015 Air Jordan 1 collaboration. Fans waited patiently for Fragment’s founder Hiroshi Fujiwara to drop a new collaboration with Jordan Brand, after a slew of other collaborations with other entities such as Louis Vuitton, Anti-Social Social Club, and Pokemon. The Air Jordan 3 Fragment brings the lighting bolt brand back to a classic Jordan model.

Following Hiroshi Fujiwara’s love for simplistic motifs, the Air Jordan 3 Fragment comes dressed in white and black. The upper features a primarily white leather upper with a black full-grain leather mudguard. This collaboration replaces the Elephant print that typically appears on a Jordan 3 with plush black leather embossed with the Fragment lighting bolt logo. The sneaker’s white midsole has the colorway’s style code and release date printed in black text. To show true unison between the two brands, the Fragment’s lighting bolt logo appears behind a translucent Jumpman, in a similar fashion to August’s Fire Red Denim 3s.

The Air Jordan 3 Fragment dropped in September of 2020 for $200.

product name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG SP Travis Scott
product desp:
The first release as part of Travis Scott's monumental partnership with Nike, the Air Jordan 1 Travis Scott breaks the conventional rules of the Air Jordan 1 design. For starters, the side Swooshes are reversed, which each tailing facing the toe. Woven tongue tags are shifted and stitched to the side of the tongue instead of the top. Also, in the collar, there is a hidden stash pocket. A one-of-a-kind design fit for a one-of-a-kind artist.

The Air Jordan 1 Travis Scott features a white leather upper with Mocha suede overlays and black leather reversed Swooshes. Hits of red on the tongue slightly contrast the design's earth tones. On the heel, a debossed Cactus Jack logo adds a custom feel. From there, a yellowed midsole and matching Mocha outsole complete the design.

The Jordan 1 Travis Scott Mocha released in May 2019 and retailed for $175.

To shop all Air Jordan 1 shoes, click here.

The Air Jordan 11 Retro Playoffs 2019 for Grade School (GS) uses the classic Black/White/Varsity Red ‘bred’ colorway introduced in 1996. The patent leather mudguard, nylon mesh upper, tongue, webbed eyestays, and rope-like laces are black. A white Nike Air logo and swoosh appear on the black insole. The black leather collar features a red-stitched Jumpman and a white 23. A black Jumpman is visible through the translucent red rubber outsole with spots of black chevrons. A carbon-fiber midfoot shank in black and gray checks enhances the white midsole.

The Air Jordan 11 Retro Playoffs 2019 GS sneaker for kids was released on December 14, 2019, at a retail price of $170.

product name: Nike ACG Mountain Fly Low Gore-Tex SE Dark Smoke Grey
model: Nike ACG Mountain Fly Low Gore-Tex SE
product desp:
The Nike ACG Mountain Fly Low Gore-Tex SE in Dark Smoke Grey features the Gore Tex technology that ensures that your feet will stay dry and comfortable.

Nike ACG Mountain Fly Low Gore-Tex SE is prepared for all types of terrain. The lightweight GORE-TEX material upper offers durability and is water-repellent, while the easy lacing system customizes the fit on the fly. Its sticky rubber outsole provides mountain-inspired traction, together with the soft React foam in the midsole.

This Nike ACG Mountain Fly Low Gore Tex SE Dark Smoke Grey was released back in June 2022 and retailed at $180.

Jordan Brand and Virgil Abloh teamed up once again to release the third silhouette in their collaborative history with the women's Jordan 4 Retro Off-White Sail (W), now available on StockX. After teasing the release of the Off-White 4 with samples in his MCA exhibit and presenting them in his Off-White FW2020 Women’s Show, Virgil Abloh finally delivered what might be the most anticipated release of 2020.

The Air Jordan 4 Sail features full-grain leather uppers with hits of mesh and translucent materials on the toebox and heel of the shoe. From there, hits of light blue on the tongue’s Jumpman and the outsole’s Nike Swoosh provide contrast to the sail colored sneaker. These women's sneakers released in July of 2020 and retailed for $200 USD.

The Reebok Shaq Attaq Orlando 2022 is a special edition sneaker that features a Cloud White leather upper with Core Black polished suede overlays.

The shoe is accented with metallic Azure blue, which animates the cushioned collar and tongue. Included on its tongue, however, is an enlarged rubber button that trips the custom fit. Branding includes Shaq’s "Dunk Man" emblem, which enhances the back heel, and Reebok's which is stitched on the oblique side of the shoe. The sneaker sits on an EVA cushioned midsole, reinforced by a graphite plate and long-lasting rubber below the heel and the forefoot.

The Reebok Shaq Attaq Orlando 2022 debuted on September 23rd, 2022. It retailed at $170.

product desp:
Jordan Brand reimagines one of the original Air Jordan 13 Low colorways as a high-top with the Air Jordan 13 Brave Blue.

Drawing inspiration from the 1998 Air Jordan 13 Low Navy, the Air Jordan 13 Brave Blue features a black tumbled leather upper with Brave Blue mesh overlays and black Durabuck underlays. At the collar, a Jumpman hologram commemorates the design's signature styling. A sculptural white and black EVA foam sole provides support for daily wear.

The Air Jordan 13 Brave Blue released in April of 2022 and retailed for $200.

The Nike Dunk Low Black features a black tumbled leather upper with smooth leather overlays and white Swooshes. From there, matching woven tongue labels and EVA foam soles complete the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Black released in May of 2022 and retailed for $100.

The Nike Dunk Low Midas Gold features a Midas Gold leather upper with Tough Red overlays and Swooshes. From there, matching woven tongue tags and soles complete the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Midas Gold released in October of 2021 and retailed for $100.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Berry Pink (Women's) was made for both comfort and utility, meaning that it can be worn to play a game of basketball or to walk around town.

This high top shoe has a berry-colored sole next to a white midsole. For the body of the shoe, there are berry-colored leather overlays that sit on top of the white base. The Nike swoosh symbol appears in black, as well as parts of the shoe near the ankle, and the Air Jordan symbol.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Berry Pink (W) for women first hit the market in January of 2022. The retail price for this specific product was $120.

The UGG Disquette Slipper Chestnut W is footwear sized for women (W) that come with plush lining and a thick outsole.

This slipper features a soft upper in a chestnut brown colorway with a rounded toe, a raised center seam, and heat-embossed UGG branding on the lateral side. This model has a sheepskin insole with a branding patch and a sheepskin collar and lining. The 1-inch platform outsole is constructed from Treadlite by UGG as well as EVA. Recycled polyester fibers bind this slipper together.

The UGG Disquette Slipper Chestnut W was released in January 2021 at a retail price of $100.

Arriving in a pastel palette similar to Easter Eggs, the women's Nike Dunk Low Easter features a light grey smooth leather upper with light purple overlays and faint pink Swooshes. A woven Nike tongue tag and embroidered heel tab adds a vintage look. From there, an off-white and purple foam sole completes the design.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Easter released in April of 2022 and retailed for $110.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Geode is a collaboration product between adidas and music icon Kanye West’s Yeezy brand. Initially released as a Yeezy supply exclusive in 2021, this colorway had a wider launch in Spring 2022.

Unique in appearance, this colorway features a lilac nylon upper, with the 700 branding on the lateral side. It also features tongues, laces, and a collar done in a charcoal hue. These highlights lie atop an enclosed Boost Black Sole Unit.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Geode was widely launched on the 19th of April, 2022. At the time of its release, this shoe commanded a retail price of $220.

product name: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 QS Purple Skeleton Halloween (2021)
product desp:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low 07 QS Skeleton Halloween 2021 features a purple leather upper with skeleton graphics on both lateral and medial sides. At the base, a semi-translucent glow-in-the-dark sole and Nike embroidery on the heel tab completes the design.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low 07 QS Skeleton Halloween 2021 released in October of 2021 and retailed for $130.

product name: Jordan 1 Mid SE Light Iron Ore (Women's)
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Light has white laces and a white tongue. At the top of the tongue, you will find the Air Jordan symbol in grey.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Light Iron Ore W has a light grey outsole, with a bright white midsole on top. A mixture of pebbled leather and canvas-like fabric is used for the rest of the body. Grey canvas panels are carefully placed on the sides, surrounding the pink leather Nike swoosh symbol.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Light Iron Ore (W) for women was initially released in February of 2022. The starting retail price for this shoe model was $135.

This Air Jordan 1 Low SE True Blue pays tribute to the original Air Jordan 3 "True Blue" and introduces elephant print to the silhouette.

The Air Jordan 1 Low SE True Blue upper is built on a white leather base with grey textured leather wrapping around the toe. The sneaker introduces an elephant print on the heel and eye stays, and blue suede adorns the collar. Black is introduced on the Swooshes, and the blue trim continues to the liner, Wings motif, and rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 1 Low SE True Blue was released in June 2022 and retailed for $110.

The Jordan 1 Low Green Toe features white, black, and Noble Green leather upper with black Swooshes and tongues. In alignment with other Bred Toe-inspired color blocked designs, the Green Toe opts for a green perforated toe box blocked in with a black leather toe wrap. A white and green Air sole completes the design.

The Jordan 1 Low Green Toe released in October of 2021 and retailed for $100.

product name: Nike SB Dunk Low Blue Raspberry
product desp:
As part of the 2022 Nike SB Fruit Pack, the Nike SB Dunk Low Blue Raspberry features a Laser Blue tumbled leather upper with Racer Blue suede overlays and University Blue Swooshes. On the inside face of the tongue, a woven label depicting a cartoon-style raspberry character adds a playful look to the silhouette. From there, a cushioned Zoom Air sole completes the design.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Blue Raspberry released in June of 2022 and retailed for $110.

product name: Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Anthracite
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Red Aqua Gold boasts a multicolor look with a leather, Durabuck, suede and denim composition. Hits of white, red, gold, aqua, and black deliver a broad palette. Similar to other colorways in the Jordan 1 Zoom Air CMFT collection, an inset Swoosh, a tongue with exposed foam edges, and a Zoom Air sole complete the design.

The Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Red Aqua Gold released in May of 2022 and retailed for $140.

product name: Jordan 1 Elevate Low SE University Blue (Women's)
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Elevate Low SE University Blue (W) for women sports a two-tone white and university blue makeup nodding to Michael Jordan’s 1982 NCAA Championship.

The Air Jordan 1 Elevate Low SE University Blue (W) features a white leather base with university blue overlays and Swooshes. The white leather extends to the tongue and liner, while underfoot, a modified chunky platform sole in white atop a uni blue rubber outsole with the outline of the Win(GS) for grade schoolers logo in the rear and cork insoles completes the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Elevate Low SE University Blue (W) was released in April 2022 and retailed for $145.

The upper of the Nike Dunk Low Michigan is made of Varsity Maize leather with Midnight Navy overlays and Swoosh logos. A woven Nike label stitched to the tongue and "NIKE" text embroidered on the heel complete the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Varsity Michigan released in June of 2021 and retailed for $100.

The New Balance 550 Salt and Papper takes on a retro-inspired silhouette and is dressed in a white, beige, and dark gray colorway.

It features a mixed upper constructed with smooth leather, mesh, and perforations in various places. Black details are visible around the N logo and the quarter trim. Other highlights include a low-cut cream collar made of mesh, 550 branding on the side close to the toe box, and NB branding on the tongue, heel, and midsole. A white midsole that sits on a rubber outsole with varying shades of gray completes the design.

The New Balance 550 Salt and Papper was released on October 19th, 2022. Initially, it retailed at $110.

With extra cushioning and support, the Nike Waffle One Summit White can be used for both walking around town or for a bit of more intense exercise.

This pair of shoes has a black sole next to a bright white midsole. The body of the shoe features colors like white, beige, and gray, with different fabrics, including suede and mesh. The iconic Nike symbol known as the Swoosh appears in white. This is a low top model that ends right at the beginning of the ankle.

The Nike Waffle One Summit White was first released in May of 2021. This model had a starting retail price of $100.

The women's exclusive Air Jordan 11 Animal Instinct (W) features a muted black Durabuck upper with animal print faux fur overlays. Metallic Jumpman logos and semi translucent outsoles add key elements true to the origins of the Jordan 11 design.

The Air Jordan 11 Animal Instinct (W) released in November of 2021 and retailed for $225.

The Nike Dunk Low Pink Oxford W is part of the Nike Low Dunk women’s shoe collection.

The design has a smooth leather upper with a light grey base, subtle pink overlays, and a Light Thistle, a pale lavender, Swoosh. It has a low-cut padded collar and a nylon tongue. The Nike Dunk Low Pink Oxford W is supported by a rubber midsole in Lemon Wash, a yellow color that makes the sidewall intentionally appear worn. The Swoosh logo is featured on the sides, and an imprinted label in Light Thistle is on the back of the heel. The sneaker has a round toe, a logo patch at the tongue, and front lace-up fastening. 

The  Nike Dunk Low Pink Oxford W debuted on 28 July 2022 and retailed at a price of $100.

product name: Nike Air Max Penny 1 All-Star Black Metallic Silver
product desp:
The Nike Air Max Penny 1 All Star Black Metallic Silver Varsity Royal is part of the brand's additional release to its footwear catalog.

The vintage hoops shoe has a black nubuck upper that is complemented by royal blue piping and a large studded Swoosh on the lateral side. Penny's 1 Cent is embossed on the rear heel, and there is additional Swoosh insignia on the toe box and tongue. A black Phylon midsole that has a dual-chambered Max Air unit tucked away in the heel completes the design.

The Nike Air Max Penny 1 All Star Black Metallic Silver Varsity Royal was launched on December 6th, 2022. The pair retailed at $200.

product name: Jordan 1 Retro High White University Blue Black (GS)
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro High White University Blue Black GS features a tumbled white leather upper with perforations on the toe box. Overlays are made of University Blue supple suede and the Swoosh and collar are black tumbled leather. The outsole is University Blue with concentric circles in the rubber. The Air midsole is white, the laces are black, and a black Wings logo accents the University Blue suede overlay on the collar.

  The grade school-sized Air Jordan 1 Retro High White University Blue Black GS, was released on March 6, 2021, at a retail price of $140.

The Nike Dunk Low Green Velvet (W), designed and sized for women, is made to offer a look of plush elegance.

The Green Velvet Nike Dunk Low for women (W) features an upper with a Dark Atomic Teal velvet base with perforations in the toe box and Dark Atomic Teal velvet overlays. The laces and the midsole provide contrast in white sail. The tongue, insole, embroidered Nike branding on the heel tab, and the rubber outsole are Dark Atomic Teal and the Nike branding on the tongue and insole are white sail. 

The Nike Dunk Low Green Velvet (W) in women’s sizing debuted on November 30, 2022 for $110 retail.

product name: Nike Kyrie Flytrap V Wolf Grey
product desp:
The Nike Kyrie Flytrap V Wolf Grey has become a celebrated addition to the basketball shoe catalog.

The upper section of this Nike Flytrap V is white mesh, with the outline of a stenciled-on silver-gray Swoosh. Criss-crossing containment straps help keep your foot in place, and collar padding is for heel lockdown. The midsole of the forefoot contains a Zoom Air unit designed to compress and spring back into place. The rubber outsole features multidirectional traction that curves up the side of the sneaker in a grey design.

The Nike Kyrie Flytrap V Wolf Grey was release on February 14th, 2022 and retailed for $90.

Yeezy added a new colorway to their expanding 380 line with the Yeezy 380 Calcite Glow, now available on StockX. While 380 releases following the Alien colorway are known for their brown, earth-toned look, the Calcite returned to the design’s roots with a ghostly vibe just in time for Halloween.

The Yeezy 380 Calcite Glow is reminiscent of the very first Yeezy 380 release, the Yeezy 380 Alien. Similar to the Alien, the Calcite Glow features a white and grey perforated Primeknit upper. The main difference between the two colorways is that the Calcite Glow primarily features white throughout, with grey detailing. Also, the Calcite comes with a translucent, glow-in-the-dark sole that is guaranteed to add some extra glow to your feet.

The Yeezy 380 Calcite Glow released in October of 2020 and retailed for $250.

The Air Jordan 6 Bordeaux features a two-tone black and grey Durabuck upper just like the original Jordan 7 Bordeaux. From there, the signature Bordeaux geometric pattern is prominent on the inner-facing tongue and sock liner. Jumpman embroidery on the heel and a semi-translucent outsole complete the retro look.

The Air Jordan 6 Bordeaux released in September of 2021 and retailed for $190.

product name: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 LV8 40th Anniversary White Black
product desp:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low 07 LV8 40th Anniversary White Black is dressed in different color schemes, with metallic gold, black, and white coming as the main tones.

The upper of this Low Nike Air Force 1 sneaker is made of white leather material with blacked-out heel tabs. The Nike logo, as well as Swooshes, are displayed on its laterals. This shoe also comes with black "AIR" printing on its white sole and has a white lace closure system.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low 07 LV8 40th Anniversary White Black had a retail price of $120 on its market debut on October 13th, 2022.

product name: Nike Air Max 1 PRM Somos Familia (Women's)

product desp:
If you are looking for a staple pair of black and white Vans for your rotation, the Vans Old Skool Black White is a popular choice. It arrives with a low-top black canvas upper with white leather Vans stripe detailing on lateral and medial sides. At the base, a white and gum waffle cup sole with a red, branded heel patch adds the finishing touch.

This model of the Vans Old Skool Black White released in 2017 and retailed for $70.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro French Blue GS is categorized under Nike’s fashion sneakers. The upper of this shoe is made of white tumbled leather, its toe of light steel grey leather, while the heel, midsole, and mudguards are all accented with "French Blue" suede.

The tongues of the Retro French Air Jordan 13 for grade-schoolers have a red Jumpman insignia that stands out clearly. The insoles also have white Jumpman logos on them. The rubber outsoles come in grey and white color schemes. The colors are a clear homage to the French flag.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro French Blue GS hit the market on the 19th of September at a retail price of $150.

The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Oatmeal W has become a celebrated addition to the women´s catalog.

This Vomero Nike Zoom model comes dressed in an Oatmeal, Sail, Pale Ivory, and Light Chocolate color scheme. The shoe features a tonal upper constructed of an open mesh base paired with leather overlays and Swooshes. Other design details include the plastic side panels and heel counter, 3M reflective hits, and the Bill Bowerman motif stamped onto the insoles, all in while atop Zoom Air cushioning.

The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Oatmeal W was made available on December 7th, 2022, retailing at $160.

product name: Jordan 4 Retro Travis Scott Cactus Jack
product desp: The only way to describe the Travis Scott Air Jordan 4 Retros properly would be to use the rappers own adlib: la flame. These Jordan 4s were made in collaboration with rapper, Travis Scott and nicknamed the "Cactus Jack" edition. Similar in design to the infamous Eminem pair, these feature a lighter shade of blue suede on the upper. Black accents, a red liner, paint splatter detailing, a white midsole and "Cactus Jack" branding on the back heel tab finish things off for this pair. These dropped in June of 2018 for $225 and came exclusively in men’s sizes. If you’re a fan of Travis Scott and the AJ 4, this pair is another must-have. Straight up!

Round Two’s Sean Wotherspoon teamed up with adidas once again in 2021 to release the adidas ZX8000 Sean Wotherspoon Super Earth. Wotherspoon and adidas started their Super Earth initiative in 2020, a project aimed at decreasing waste through pattern efficiency, recycled material selection, and vegan-first design. The first silhouette to have the Super Earth moniker was the adidas Superstar, and its design emphasized the beauty of vegan-friendly leather. As part of adidas’ A-ZX collection, Wotherspoon continued his upcycled philosophy and approach to sneakers with the ZX8000 model.

The adidas ZX8000 Sean Wotherspoon Super Earth is a collage of different upcycled textiles, each with its own distinct look and texture. The upper is composed of a mix of flannel, denim, and canvas, similar to the range of materials one would find in Wotherspoon’s Round Two Vintage stores. Green plaid flannel makes up the design’s toe wrap and heel tab, while brown and red canvases cover the vamp, side panels, eyestays, and heel. On the side panel, canvas Three Stripes branding overlaps white and neon green flower embroidery. Lastly, a clear heel unit, "Super Earth" script on the tongue, and a cream Torsion sole round out this Earth-friendly design.

The adidas ZX8000 Sean Wotherspoon Super Earth released in April of 2021 and retailed for $140.

The Air Jordan 12 Low Golf Playoff, with radiating stitched lines on the upper's black leather and white lizard-textured overlays, the mid-top model features a basic two-tone color scheme. 

The molded eyelets of the shoe have a metallic silver sheen, while the tongue, which has an embroidered Jumpman, and the webbing heel loop have color-popped crimson embellishments. Full-length Zoom Air cushioning, a shank plate made of carbon fiber, and an outsole made of rubber with herringbone grip pods under the forefoot and heel are featured.

The Air Jordan 12 Low Golf Playoff was released on the market on October 18th, 2022, and originally retailed at $220.

product name: Jordan 1 Low SE Wear Away Yellow
Puma LaMelo Ball MB.02 Lunar New Year Jade
product desp:
Puma and LaMelo Ball are celebrating Lunar New Year on court with the release of their Puma LaMelo Ball MB.02 Lunar New Year Jade sneakers. Lunar New Year celebrates its year of the rabbit in 2023.

LaMelo Balls Puma MB.02 basketball sneaker is dressed in a Jade green colorway with gold accents. The limited edition sneakers are made up of a breathable mesh material that sits atop jade rubber outsole.In Chinese culture, jade symbolizes well-being, longevity and good luck, making it the perfect choice for this MB.02 colorway.

The Puma LaMelo Ball MB.02 Lunar New Year Jade released February 3, 2023, with a retail price of $140.

product name: Nike Air Structure OG White Neo Teal
product desp:
Nike celebrated the 30th Anniversary of its Air Structure running series by reviving the Nike Air Structure OG. The Nike Air Structure originally debuted in 1991 as a solution for runners who battled with over-pronation, the motion of a runner’s foot rolling inward as they run. The Air Structure line has since seen over 20 models, making it one of the oldest running series in Nike’s history. Nike nodded to the line’s roots with the revamped Air Structure OG.

The upper of the Nike Air Structure OG is composed of white mesh with grey, black, and Neo Teal Durabuck overlays. Hits of red are prominent on the tongue with Nike branding on the heel, and surrounding the Air unit. A white and grey midsole and black outsole wrap up this retro model.

The Nike Air Structure OG released in March of 2021 and retailed for $120.

product name: Jordan 1 Mid SE Metallic Gold Black (GS)
New Balance 2002R Black Dark Grey White
Nike Dunk Low Multiple Swooshes White Washed Teal (Women's)
Nike Air Bakin SP Supreme Black Gradient
Nike Air Max Plus Black Tour Yellow
Nike Air Max 95 LX Reflective Safari (Women's)
Nike Dunk High White Sand Drift Brown (Women's)
Jordan 1 Retro High OG Lucky Green (GS)
Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Bart Simpson
product desp:
While the Nike SB Dunk Low Bart Simpson is not an official collaboration with The Simpsons, it channels color inspiration to the rambunctious character and follows a similar format to the Nike SB Dunk High Marge Simpson and the Nike SB Dunk Low Homer Simpson.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Bart Simpson features a yellow leather upper with orange Durabuck overlays and a white Swoosh. Hits of blue on the sock liner and outsole add a cool-toned contrast to the shoe's warm palette. At the base, a Zoom sole provides comfort and support.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Bart Simpson released in May of 2022 and retailed for $100.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Sonics 2021 is back in a Seattle Supersonics themed colorway: noble green, pollen, and white.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Sonics 2021 comes constructed in a leather build featuring a white base with green overlays, laces, tongue labels, liner, and rubber outsole. Highlighting the shoe are pollen hits on the ankle collar and Jumpman branding, while white continues on the tongues, insoles, and midsole. The Swoosh appears on the lateral side in green, and the ball and Win(GS) for grade schoolers logo appears in white.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Sonics 2021 in November 2021 and retailed for $115.

Jordan Brand offered a spin-off of the 2001 Air Jordan 3 Mocha with the women's exclusive Air Jordan 3 Dark Mocha.

Also referred to as the Jordan 3 " Neopolitan" for its colorway's resemblance to the popular Italian ice cream, the women's Air Jordan 3 Dark Mocha features a white tumbled leather upper with Dark Mocha Elephant Print overlays and pale pink eyelets. Next, a TPU heel tab prominently featuring the Jumpman logo adds a retro feel. At the base, a white, pale pink, and brown Air sole ties the look together.

The women's Air Jordan 3 Dark Mocha (W) released in May of 2022 and retailed for $200.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Polaroid draws inspiration from the color spectrum found in Polaroid's logo and the casing of its instant film. Atop a black Durabuck upper, a triple-layered Swoosh creates a rainbow effect by overlapping blue and red patent leather Swooshes with a yellow transparent Swoosh. At the heel, white patent leather nods to the composition of Polaroid's instant film. From there, color spectrum embroidery on the toe and co-branded embroidery at the heel complete the design.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Polaroid released in April of 2022 and retailed for $120.

Like the original 2001 design, the gradeschool Air Jordan 11 Retro Cool Grey 2021 GS boasts a mid-top with a grey nubuck upper. This amazing colorway also boasts a white pylon cushioning boosted with a compact Air sole unit and strengthened with a translucent rubber outsole, an elegant "23" on its textile heel tab, and an embroidered white Jumpman logo on its lateral ankle.

The gradeschool Air Jordan 11 Retro Cool Grey 2021 GS was released on 12th November 2021. It retails at $185.

product name: Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70 Hi Comme des Garcons PLAY White
product desp:
With a look inspired by the Converse Chuck Taylors of the ‘70s, the Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70s Hi Comme des Garcons PLAY White has a high-top that blends the collab branding and collaboration. Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70s Hi Comme des Garcons PLAY White has a white canvas upper with double stitching and shiny metal eyelets. It also features heart icons on the sidewall. The lower part of the shoe mostly features a vulcanized rubber midsole and outsole.

Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70s Hi Commes des Garcons PLAY White was released in January 2019 and retailed at a price of $125.

The Air Jordan 11 Retro Cherry 2022 PS is a preschool release in a white, black, and varsity red color scheme.

The upper is constructed with ballistic mesh in white and a varsity red patent leather mudguard. Varsity red is also featured on the signature Jumpman logo embroidered on the lateral ankle and the padded collar lining. Other details of this mid-top model include ‘23’ branding on the heel counter and a lace-up closing system with white laces. A white phylon midsole rests on a translucent herringbone-patterned rubber outsole with AIR units.

The Air Jordan 11 Retro Cherry 2022 PS was first made available on December 10th, 2022, retailing at $100.

The Nike Dunk Low PRM Halloween features a Sail leather upper with black overlays and orange Swooshes. On the black overlays, subtle graphics of eyes from creatures of the night are painted that can glow in the dark. A glow-in-the-dark outsole and woven tongue tag complete this Halloween design.

The Nike Dunk Low PRM Halloween released in October of 2021 and retailed for $110.

product name: Nike Zoom Cortez SP sacai White University Red Blue
product desp:
The Nike Cortez 40 Sacai White University Red Blue is a sneaker that came as a collaboration between the Japanese fashion brand Sacai and Nike.

The Nike Cortez 40 Sacai in Red and Blue has double-stacked detailing, technical enhancements, and a blue color scheme. It has a sharply-lined midsole with an extended slab of foam on the heel and a puck-like exposed Zoom Air unit on the forefoot. The top half is a mixture of leather and suede. The sneaker features two swooshes, heel overlays, tongues, and a second collar, rising slightly above its counterpart.

The Nike Cortez 40 Sacai White University Red Blue retailed at $160 upon its release date on the 31st of August, 2022.

product name: Jordan 1 Low Triple White Tumbled Leather
product desp:
Drawing from the original 1985 low-top silhouette, the Air Jordan 1 Low Triple White Tumbled Leather features an all-leather, all-white finish. The Air Jordan 1 Low Triple White Tumbled Leather brings a clean white look and colorway to the low-top construction. The sneaker’s upper is made from a mix of full-grain and tumbled leather for textural depth, and the lightly padded nylon tongue provides a comfortable fit. The Jumpman replaces the common "Nike" logo on the tongue tag, and the stitched Wings logo appears large on the heel panel.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Triple White Tumbled Leather was released in April, 2020, and retailed for $90.

The Nike Dunk Low Teal Zeal (Women's) offers a vibrant palette with a smooth white leather upper and bright teal tumbled leather overlays and Swooshes. Hits of bright yellow on the woven tongue label and outsole add a warm contrast. Nike heel embroideries nod to the original 1985 design, adding the finishing touch.

The Nike Dunk Low Teal Zeal (Women's) released in July of 2022 and retailed for $110.

On the heels of the Air Jordan 1 Low Coconut Milk W, you will also find black detailing. This is a low-top model and has the standard Air Jordan tread.

The sole of the Air Jordan 1 Low Coconut Milk W is a cream color and sits right below the bright white midsole. The majority of the rest of the shoe is made out of the same cream color, with the exception being the black Nike swoosh symbol that is on the side.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Coconut Milk (W) for women had a starting release date of November 2021. It was released at an initial retail price of $100.

product name: Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Crater Purple
product desp:
Launched by Jordan Brand in April 2022, Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Crater Purple became one of Air Jordan 1 Zoom CMFT offerings.

Compared to the Jordan 1, Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Crater Purple’s main difference is the sole’s full-length Zoom unit. The Zoom unit promotes comfort by ensuring a softer and more responsive cushioning. Its design features a white leather base with an overlaying purple and cut-out swooshes. It further features; Zoom Air branded tongues, black wings, a rubber outsole on top of a Nike speckled white midsole, and collars.

 On its release date, Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Crater Purple retailed at $140. DISCLAIMER: Purple may bleed onto white canvas when exposed to water.

product name: Nike LeBron 18 Low Wile E. vs Roadrunner Space Jam
product colour: Wile E. vs Roadrunner Space Jam
product desp:
The LeBron 18 Low Wile E. vs. Roadrunner pays homage to the iconic Looney Tunes characters Wile E. Coyote and Bugs Bunny. The right shoe features a tonal upper with "ACME" contraptions placed throughout the upper. The other shoe nods to Roadrunner with its tonal blue upper and dust cloud graphics.

The Nike LeBron 18 Low Wile E. vs. Roadrunner released in July of 2021 and retailed for $160.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Black Grey Pink arrives dressed in a mix of black, grey, pink, and white.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Black Grey Pink features a white toe box with black on the side panels, tongues, laces, liner, Win(GS) for grade schoolers logo, and rubber outsole, while grey leathers are affixed to the toe, eye stays, and heel. Highlighting the shoe are contrasting pink accents on the branded areas, Swooshes, and stitching along the white midsole to complete the design. Underfoot, a white midsole and black outsole wrap up the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Black Grey Pink was released in April 2022 and retailed for $110.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Island Green (Women's) is another colorway of the Air Jordan 1 sneakers that first made their debut in 1985.

They are high-top sneakers with a lace-up closure design with white laces. The primary color of the shoe is white with island green highlights on the sides where the laces go through, round the heel of the shoe, and at the front where the sole is attached. The Air Jordan 1 Mid Island Green (Women's) also has the Nike Swoosh on the side, the Air Jordan logo on the outer ankle, and the Jumpman logo on the tongue.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Island Green (Women's) was released for retail at the price of $115 in July 2020.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Washed Denim (GS) for grade schoolers has blue laces that cover the white tongue. The shoe has the standard Nike tread and level of cushioning.

This model is made up of a bright royal blue sole and a classic white midsole. The base is also white, covered in a pattern that features splashes of black, gray, blue, and white. The Nike swoosh symbol can be seen on the side of the shoe in blue.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Washed Denim (GS) for grade schoolers for grade schoolers first was released in April of 2022. The initial retail price for the item was $80.

The New Balance 550 White Nightwatch Green is the new addition to the New Balance colorway collection.

The leather sneakers have a white background with yellow and green accents to add depth to the design. The recognizable N emblem is located on the medial and lateral surfaces in addition to the 550 markings. Additional features include a perforated toe box, basketball branding at the tongue, and ankle padding. A white cushioned midsole completes the look. The tongues are finished off with further New Balance designs and basketball images. White sole components with two-toned rubber outsoles nestle beneath the design.

The New Balance 550 White Nightwatch Green debuted on October 19, 2022, and retailed at $100.

The Nike Dunk Low SE Jackpot GS is a low-cut sneaker with hints of grey, white, blue, and red.

A product of elite designers, this shoe boasts a leather upper with a white base, grey overlays, and a scratch-off Swoosh with a hidden colorway beneath. The leather upper is held together by the shoe’s white midsole and grey outsole. This shoe’s midsole consists of cushioning material for improved comfort, while its outsole is patterned for improved grip. Additionally, for enhanced breathability, it features perforations on its forefoot.

The Nike Dunk Low SE Jackpot GS was released on the 31st of August, 2022. At the time, its retail price was $80.

product name: Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Black Yellow
product desp:
The Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Black University Gold is a collaboration between Nike and Drake’s NOCTA sublevel.

The Nike Hot Step Air Terra has pebbled black leather uppers marked with reflective 3M hits on the side panels and down the tongues. The shoe has contrasting bright accents in the form of mini Swooshes at the lateral heel regions and NOCTA markings on the rears and the tongues. The sneaker has black rope laces, sculpted sole units with large Air units, specially printed insoles, and G-TEK traction rubber outsoles.

The Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Black University Gold was released on September 16, 2022, with a retail price of $180.

The women's Jordan 1 Mid Wolf Grey Aluminum (W) features a white leather upper with Wolf Grey Durabuck overlays and an Aluminum Swoosh. From there, a Jumpman woven tongue label and icy translucent sole completes the design.

The women's Jordan 1 Mid Wolf Grey Aluminum (W) released in July of 2021 and retailed for $115.

Hype for the new Air Jordan 4 Taupe Haze started brewing when the teasers of the sneakers surfaced, with sneakerheads noting their similarities to Travis Scott’s unreleased Air Jordan 4 Olive. Despite being compared to such a hyped sneaker, the Air Jordan 4 Taupe Haze has characteristics that allow it to stand out on its own.

The Air Jordan 4 Taupe Haze features a unique design that elevates the popular Jordan model. The upper holds cracked textures on the forefoot, midfoot, and tongue, with lighter shades of Taupe Haze under the top coat. From there, hits of black appear on the outsole, midsole, and eyelets. An Infrared Jumpman logo on the tongue brightens up the tonal sneaker and completes its overall design.

The Air Jordan 4 Taupe Haze dropped in February of 2021 for $200.

The Nike Dunk Low Dark Beetroot sports a dark, pattern that consists of black, beetroot/aubegine and has bright accents in white.

The upper section of this Low Nike Dunk model is made of a dark beetroot-colored tumbled leather with perforations in the toe box. The tumbled leather overlays, sock liner, and insole appear in a slightly lighter tone. The stitched-on Swoosh, the laces, and the Nike branding on the tongue, insole, and heel tab provide stark contrast in white. The midsole is also white and the outsole boasts a rubber material.

The Nike Dunk Low Dark Beetroot was originally released on September 20, 2020 with a retail price of $120.

product name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Light Fusion Red
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Light Fusion Red features a white leather upper with Light Fusion Red overlays and Laser Orange on the Swoosh and ankle wrap. A woven Nike label stitched atop the tongue completes the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Light Fusion Red released in June of 2021 and retailed for $170.

product name: Jordan 1 Retro High Pine Green Black
product desp:
Jordan Brand added new colors to a classic silhouette with the Jordan 1 Retro High Pine Green Black, now available on StockX. This colorway draws inspiration from the Jordan 1 Retro High Pine Green from 2019, only this time the entire upper features black and pine green hues.

This Jordan 1 High is comprised of a black tumbled leather upper with green leather overlays. A Gym Red embroidered tongue tag, sail midsole, and pine green outsole completes this design. These sneakers released in February of 2020 and retailed for $170.

If you are looking for the Jordan 1 Retro High Pine Green 2018 click HERE.

product name: Nike Air Zoom Flight 95 OG Black Metallic Silver (2022)
product desp:
The Nike Air Zoom Flight 95 Black Metallic Silver 2022 returns in its original black, white, and metallic silver color scheme.

The Nike Air Zoom Flight 95 Black Metallic Silver 2022 is crafted from black nubuck upper with carbon fiber accents in the white Zoom circles found on the midsole to the sidewalk. Swoosh branding hits at the ankle, toe box, and insoles, and there are two-toned laces, and ‘Flight’ branding on the heel pull tabs. Underfoot, Zoom Air cushioning does the rest.

The Nike Air Zoom Flight 95 Black Metallic Silver 2022 was released in May 2022 and retailed for $160.

This fresh take on one of the original New Balance styles, the New Balance 2002R Nightwatch Green comes in a rich forest green that will add a pop of color to any outfit. With extra cushioning and support in the sole, you can easily use these shoes for either exercising or simply walking throughout town.

The New Balance 2002R Nightwatch Green is embellished with leather accents and has mesh pieces to help with breathability. There are also soft-to-touch suede overlays that help to add texture and depth to the model. 

Initially released in February of 2022, the New Balance 2002R Nightwatch Green was sold at a starting retail price of $150.

product name: Nike Dunk Low Velvet Brown Black
product desp:
The Nike Dunk Low Velvet Brown Black has an upper half repleted in a minor tone. Solid black covers the leather toe boxes, collars, quarters, and shoelaces as a dominant tone.

The Nike Dunk Low Velvet Brown Black has Swooshes and overlays across your forefoot, and its heels are raised, having a croc-like texture and colored in a brown velvet tone. To complete the shoe’s design, it has a dusted gum bottom.  
   
   Since its debut in April 2022, Nike Dunk Low Velvet Brown Black has been among the celebrated colorways in the Dunk Low catalog. The Nike Dunk Low Velvet Brown Black retailed at $100.

Air Jordan 4 Retro Military Black TD shows similar color blocking and materials of the OG "Military Blue" colorway from 1989.

Air Jordan 4 Retro Military Black TD has a smooth white leather upper, bolstered with forefoot overlays in grey suede. Its TPU eyelets have black accents that contrast its white upper. It features a molded heel tab and a Jumpman logo display on its woven tongue tag. The shoe also features lightweight cushioning, a two-tone polyurethane midsole, and an enhanced Air-sole unit beneath the heel.

The toddlers’ Air Jordan 4 Retro Military Black was released on 31st May 2022 at a retail price of $200.

The Nike Air Max 90 Bacon is still one of the most highly sought-after Air Max runners of all time. So much so that Nike brought back the 2004 design to celebrate Air Max Day in 2021. It is not often that Nike retros collaborations, while most rarely resurface. But with its continuously growing fan base and pleas from Air Max fans to revive the 16-year-old colorway, Nike brought back the sneaker in its OG form.

The Nike Air Max 90 Bacon returns with all of the design qualities from the 2004 collaboration with Dave’s Quality Meat’s creator, David Ortiz. Mimicking the different shades of colors that appear from raw bacon, the sneaker is composed of various shades of brown, red, pink, and off-white. With a combination of suede, tumbled leather, and mesh, this Air Max 90 brings a luxe feel to the traditional 1990 model.

The Nike Air Max 90 Bacon released in March of 2021 for $140.

The Air Jordan 5 Retro Dark Concord (Gradeschool) is Jordan Brand’s new colorway that was released as part of its Fall 2022 lineup.

The new Air Jordan 5 Retro Dark Concord (Gradeschool) is features a dark concord, white, and black color scheme. The offering features a smooth, white leather top that is contrasted by bright purple hits. The white leather top is then paired with the concord contrasted accents and a sock-liner. The design is completed by reflective tongues and a black midsole on top of an icy translucent outsole.

During its release in August 2022, Air Jordan 5 Retro Dark Concord (Gradeschool) retailed at $150.

The Nike Dunk High Lakers decks out the iconic basketball shoe in the colors of LA's NBA championship team.

Court purple overlays and a matching Swoosh are placed over an amber foundation on the soft leather upper. The high-top shoe has a woven Nike tag on top of the breathable nylon tongue and a perforated toe box, in addition to the color blocking that is reminiscent of the original models. A long-lasting rubber cup sole is joined by white sides and a sturdy purple rubber outsole.

The Nike Dunk High Lakers debuted on August 16, 2022. It originally retailed at $125.

The Timberland 6-Inch Black Nubuck features a black Nubuck leather construction which comes from top-grain calfskin or cowhide. The leather is layered on the collar to create comfort and protect the feet from outside elements. Timberland also includes anti-fatigue technology that absorbs sudden impact and returns that energy to where it came from.

The Timberland 6-Inch Black Nubuck released in January of 2018 and retailed for $190.

product name: Jordan 13 Retro Obsidian Powder Blue White

The Air Jordan 13 Obsidian arrives in similar color blocking as the renowned Jordan 13 He Got Game. It features a white tumbled leather upper with dark Obsidian underlays and a light blue Jumpman tongue embroidery. In traditional fashion, a holographic bubble on the ankle adds the finishing touch.

The Air Jordan 13 Obsidian released in September of 2021 and retailed for $190.

The Nike Dunk Low Two Toned Grey (Preschool) has the perforated toebox that the brand has become so famous for. White shoe laces lay on top of a white tongue that has splashes of grey and blue.

On this model, you can find a grey sole, white midsole, and a white base for the body. On top of the white base, there are patches of grey leather. The famous swoosh symbol on the side is made from white leather.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High Black White Light Smoke Grey GS features a black, white, and light smoke grey leather upper along the toe box and the sides of the silhouette. The upper is further wrapped in overlays of smoke grey that sit on top of a white midsole and dark black outsole, and a grey Swoosh logo and Air Jordan badges on the sides of the shoe complete the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High Black White Light Smoke Grey GS released in May of 2021 and retailed for $130.

product name: adidas NMD R1 Primeblue Triple Black

The Jordan 1 Mid Chicago Toe features a black, white, and Gym Red leather and nylon upper. From there, a nylon tongue featuring a black "Jumpman" logo set and a white midsole complete the design.

The Jordan 1 Mid Chicago Toe released in April of 2020 and retailed for $115.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Stealth French Blue W features a color-blocking pattern. It is designed with a leather upper in white and French blue, with a mesh tongue in stealth grey.

The tongue is embellished with a matching blue Jumpman, and the heel is embroidered with a vintage Wings logo. A rubber cup sole that has encapsulated Air Sole cushioning in the heel supports the low top. It all sits on a white leather base.

Additional details like the embroidered mini-Swoosh on the toe box and gum outsole offer nostalgic appeal.

Jordan Brand looked to the stars as inspiration for the Jordan 4 Retro Starfish (W). This Women’s exclusive blends style with functionality through its use of technical materials that are commonly found on astronaut suits.

The upper of the women's Jordan 4 Retro Starfish (W) is composed of black metallic mesh with hits of Starfish orange outlining the shoe’s paneling. Matte TPU heel tabs and wings alongside black netting on the quarter panels nod to classic Jordan 4 features. Since its launch in 1992, New Balance 530 Ivory has become a popular unisex sneaker due to its performance running shoe design.

New Balance 530 Ivory's upper is made of synthetic leather, while the midsole is produced through a cold cement process. New Balance 530 Ivory's design is ivory, white, and black, with a style code of MR530SH. The sneaker weighs 339 grams (12 oz.) and features a lace-up closure. 2020 brings another Union LA collaboration with Jordan Brand with the Air Jordan 4 Union LA Off Noir. Similar to 2018’s unique construction, the product of this second partnership isn’t immune to creative design.

The Air Jordan 11 Space Jam has released twice since it first appeared on the feet of Michael Jordan in the 1995 NBA Playoffs. The 2016 Jordan 11 Space Jam marks the third time that this iconic shoe and immensely popular colorway hit retail shelves. The Black, Dark Concord and White colorway received the Space Jam nickname due to the product placement in Space Jam the movie that released in 1996. With 2016 being the 20th anniversary and the rumors of LeBron James playing a role, the Jordan 11 Space Jam captures the spotlight once again with a retro release. After early speculations had the colors and shape of the silhouette slightly off, official images seem to have a majority of sneakerheads anticipating this release. If pre-release action is any indicator, the 2016 Air Jordan 11 Space Jam is one of the biggest release.

The Nike Air Huarache Triple Black 2021 falls under the gap of Nike sneakers. This sneaker features a midsole forefoot flex ridges that are deeply and highly sculpted.

The Nike Air Huarache Triple Black 2021 is entirely made up of synthetic leather and a nylon combo that is paired to the neoprene bootie. The sneaker also features a flexible molded heel structure. This sneaker’s entire upper part is made up of an encapsulated Air unit. The entire sneaker is black colored.

The Nike Air Huarache Triple Black 2021 was made available at the retail price of $120 on August 5th, 2021.

product desp:
After a preview at New York Fashion Week, Tokyo fashion label AMBUSH and Nike teamed up once again to deliver a new colorway with the Nike Dunk High Ambush Active Fuchsia. The collaboration nods to the culture surrounding transportation in Japan, which explains the re-imagined proportions on the silhouette that almost make it look aerodynamic.

The Nike Dunk High Ambush Fuchsia arrives with an Active Fuschia leather upper and an exaggerated Swoosh that protrudes the heel. Aside from the re-imagined Swoosh, other features differentiate this design from traditional Nike Dunks like a raised heel counter with significant separation on the back of the shoe, revealing a larger amount of Active Fuschia leather paneling, and an extended plastic unit donning Ambush branding encapsulates the heel. An exposed foam tongue, Active Fuchsia sole, and co-branded tongue tag add the finishing touches to the avant-garde design.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Pine Green GS is made of three major colors that define its look: white, pine green, as well as black.

The shoe also boasts a Nike Swoosh that comes in a black hue. The design of this model is completed by a perforated toe cap.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Pine Green GS made its debut in the market on February 1, 2020, it was recommended to retail for $90.
