The kid-sized Air Jordan 12 Retro Playoffs 2022 GS was released on March 11, 2022, at a retail price of $150.

The Kids Air Jordan 1 Mid Banned 2020 offers a mid-top take on Michael Jordan’s first signature shoe, the controversial Jordan 1 High Banned.

On the upper of the Kids Air Jordan 1 Mid Banned 2020’s ankle flaps, Swoosh, heel counters, and toe boxes are all constructed with red leather. Black laces, leather medial side and toe panels, and tongue create a contrasted look to the design. A white midsole and red outsole complete the design.

The Kids Air Jordan 1 Mid Banned 2020 released in November of 2020 and retailed for $90.

product name: Jordan 1 Mid French Blue Fire Red
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Mid French Blue Fire Red is part of the Nike Jumpman Brand collection.
​​
​The colorway includes a lightblue-and-white leather suede accent base. Gray leather makes up the side Swoosh and rubber outsole. The upper of the sneaker is slightly lower as well, but the red branding, together with the blue padding and laces, contrast with the shoe's general design to give it its overall appearance. Additionally, it features the medial and lateral sidewalls' grey Swoosh and Michael Jordan's Jumpman logo at the tongue's top.​
​​
​The Air Jordan 1 Mid French Blue Fire Red debuted on September 20, 2022, and originally retailed at $135.

To celebrate Air Max Day 2022, Nike delivered the Nike Air Max 1 Premium Blueprint.

The North American-exclusive Nike Air Max 1 Blueprint highlights the silhouettes worldwide appeal and global impact. It features a white mesh upper with light blue Durabuck and tumbled leather overlays. Each Swoosh features a grid blue pattern, nodding to the composition of blueprints. At the heel, a globe embroidery and classic Nike Air logo completes the design.

The Nike Air Max 1 Blueprint released in March of 2022 and retailed for $160.

product name: Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf Shattered Backboard
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf Shattered Backboard follows an Air Jordan series of colorways that pays attention to color blocking.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Golf Shattered Backboard features Sail tumbled leather panels, black overlays, and matching nylon tongue, lining, and laces. The shoe has an air midsole cushioning. It features a tangerine shade over the perforated toe, heel, and ankle. It also has nubuck overlays in an inky tone with a contrasting white pebbled leather side panel.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf Shattered backboard was released in January 2022 at a retail price of $140.

product name: Nike Blazer Low 77 Vintage White Black
product desp:
The Nike Blazer Low 77 Vintage White Black returns with its low-profile style, and heritage basketball looks.

The nearly 1-to-1 remake of the Nike Blazer Low 77 Vintage White Black features crisp leather on the upper with soft suede and synthetic details for added durability and throwback styling. The ultra-clean colors, simple lines, and low-cut, padded collar continue the look, which is wrapped up by an outsole fused with the midsole. The solid rubber outsole with herringbone pattern adds traction, durability, and heritage styling.

The Nike Blazer Low 77 Vintage White Black was released in December 2020 and originally retailed for $85.

DISCLAIMER: US and UK sizing is the same and does not require any conversion.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Pure is constructed of Pure EVA foam with a soft footbed that offers an immediate step in comfort. An outsole with accentuated grooves for traction and support adds the finishing touches to the design.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Pure released in April of 2021 and retailed for $60.

Jordan Brand is reaching harder than MJ on Space Jam for the sneaker of the year crown by releasing the Jordan 11 Retro Concord (2018). This Iconic Jordan 11 colorway is showcasing a white upper with black accents, white midsole, and a freezing cold translucent sole. These sneakers released in December 2018 and retailed for $220. Revisit the dominant legacy MJ left behind and grab a pair on StockX today.

The Air Jordan 5 Retro Gore Tex Off Noir W was a celebrated addition to the women´s catalog.

This sneaker features a faded black upper built with the waterproof Gore-Tex technology. Fire Red accents are displayed throughout the upper with "Gore-Tex" and "23" branding on the side heels. Other details include a TPU mesh on the side panel, 3M reflective Silver tongues, the Jumpman Logo on the heel counter and tongue, and shark teeth motif on the midsole. A translucent outsole with AIR units completes the design in a Noir colorway.

The Air Jordan 5 Retro Gore Tex Off Noir W was made available on November 3rd, 2022 retailing at $220.

Jordan Brand brought back a beloved Cool Grey from their archives with the Air Jordan 3 Cool Grey. The Cool Grey colorway has been prominently featured on some of Jumpman’s most prolific silhouettes, most notably the Air Jordan 11.

The upper of the Jordan 3 Cool Grey is constructed of a Cool Grey Durabuck with classic Elephant Print mudguards on the toe and heel. Hits of Sport Red and Orange Peel are located on the tongue, eyelets, Air bag, and heel tab. Instead of traditional "Nike Air" branding on the heel, this model stays true to its 2007 rendition and features a Jumpman logo. A white and dark grey sole completes this retro design.

The Air Jordan 3 Cool Grey released in February of 2021 and retailed for $190.

product name: Jordan 1 Mid SE Rush Orange Crimson Bliss (Women's)
product desp:
The Air Jordan 1 Mid Orange Black (Women) falls under Nike’s Sports sneakers category for women. The sneaker is dressed in various color schemes, such as rush orange, crimson bliss, sail, and black.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Orange Black (Women) is made from leather with most of its upper in orange. It has black panels on its sides and a Wings logo. This sneaker features nylon tongues, and its toe box is made of a lighter tone. The sneaker’s rubber outsole and the Swooshes are orange in color, while the midsole comes in white.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Orange Black (Women) was released on June 1st, 2022, and retailed at $135.

product name: Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Rush Maroon (with Bracelet)
product desp:
The Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Noise Rush Maroon features a grey mesh upper with smooth maroon leather overlays and wave-shaped mudguards. A yellowed Air sole with a brown outsole adds the finishing touches.

The Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Noise Rush Maroon released in November of 2021 and retailed for $160.

With simple details, the Air Jordan 1 Low Triple Black is known for offering plenty of comfort and support, making it a convenient shoe to wear on the basketball court, or during everyday life.

This model is a fresh take on an original style that first debuted in 1985. It is made out of smooth and pebbled black leather, featuring the iconic perforated toe box. There is subtle stitching outlining the Nike swoosh symbol on the side.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Triple Black was first released in January of 2021. This pair of shoes had a starting retail price of $100.

product name: Nike Dunk High Washed Denim Pack (Women's)
product desp:
The Nike Dunk High Denim (Women's) arrives with a tumbled white leather upper with bleached denim overlays and smooth red leather Swooshes. To coincide with the design's throwback aesthetic, a slightly yellowed sole provides an aged look.

The Nike Dunk High Denim (Women's) released in June of 2022 and retailed for $125.

The Air Jordan 5 Retro Raging Bulls Red 2021 GS features a Varsity Red suede upper with quarter panel netting on the side wall. A red-on-red embroidered number 23, black leather molded eyelets, red laces, and a silver tongue edged with black complete the look. The outer sole is gray, black, and white. The midsole is black with jagged splashes of white and red and visible air cushioning. Iconic Jumpman logos appear on the tongue, heel, and outer sole.

  This grade-school-sized Air Jordan 5 Retro Raging Bulls Red 2021 GS was released on April 10, 2021 at a retail price of $140.

The Air Jordan 2 Retro Low Two 18 is a collaborative design that pays homage to Detroit - the Motor City of America.

The upper of this Retro Air Jordan 2 model features a low profile, a Rocky Tan nubuck base with British Tan darker tan overlays that boasts reptile patterning on the medial side. Team Royal and Gym-Red piping, tortoise shell eyelets, and an embossed Wings logo complete the look of this upper section. The midsole features an Air-sole unit, the outsole is translucent rubber, and the insole features a map of the Detroit metro area.

The Air Jordan 2 Retro Low Two 18 was released on October 21, 2022 at a retail price of $200.

The women's Air Jordan 1 Mid Kentucky Blue (W) boasts a full leather upper comprised of white leather and Royal Blue leather overlays. The white leather covers the toes, ankles, and sides. The iconic colorway also boasts Nike Swoosh logos on its sides, the legendary Jumpman logo on its royal blue tongue, a white rubber midsole, and a royal blue outsole hardened to improve the sneaker’s durability.

The women's Air Jordan 1 Mid Kentucky Blue (W) was released in September of 2021 and retailed for $120.

product name: Nike SB Dunk Low HUF New York City
product desp:
The Nike SB Dunk Low HUF New York City was a collaborative edition that pays homage to the 20th anniversary of the streetwear brand HUF. 

This Low SB Dunk model by Nike comes with a "cut and peel" system on the navy blue tumbled leather quarter panel on the lateral side that reveals blue and white tie-dye canvas. The NYC skyline on the heel glows in the dark. It also includes embroidered heel tabs, a perforated toe box and an inscription that reads "Forever" in the rear section.

The Nike SB Dunk Low HUF New York City debuted on November 16th, 2022 with a retail price set at $130.

The New Balance 550 Vintage Indigo Beige is a retro-inspired sneaker that was released as part of the sports collection by the American brand.

This sneaker features a beige and white mesh and leather upper with hints of vintage indigo on the tongues, ankles, and branding. Other details include the trademark "N" logo on the sides, "550" labeling on the laterals, New Balance basketball branding on the tongue tag, midsole and heel, and a lace-up closing system. The design is finished with a white midsole that sits on an Indigo rubber outsole with a linear pattern.

The New Balance 550 Vintage Indigo Beige made its debut on December 14th, 2022, retailing at $110.
